1
00:00:56,097 --> 00:00:58,183
Babe, are you out here?

2
00:00:58,516 --> 00:00:59,350
Yeah.

3
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:01,310
Thought you might be.

4
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:02,687
I have to go soon.

5
00:01:02,688 --> 00:01:04,022
Okay. Okay, I'm comin'.

6
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:06,523
Come say goodbye to me.

7
00:01:06,524 --> 00:01:08,025
- Coffee?
- Good call.

8
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:09,318
Would you make one
while I finish packing?

9
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,361
Of course.

10
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:25,168
Car should be here in a minute.

11
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:30,005
Oh, thank you.

12
00:01:30,006 --> 00:01:31,048
Oh, my God.

13
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:33,050
West bound
is experiencing heavy traffic...

14
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:34,509
starting from the 610

15
00:01:34,510 --> 00:01:36,261
Garret road exit
and stretching...

16
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:38,513
What am I gonna do without
your coffee for five days?

17
00:01:38,514 --> 00:01:41,059
- They have coffee in London.
- Do they?

18
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:43,602
You sound really sure
for somebody who's never been.

19
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:45,771
Five days?
I thought you said four.

20
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:48,066
Yeah. Four days there, and then
I'm back on the overnight.

21
00:01:49,025 --> 00:01:50,110
Oh, right.

22
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:52,696
You can still come, you know.

23
00:01:53,654 --> 00:01:54,613
I can't.

24
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:57,616
I mean, there's somethin'
I'm tryin' to untangle at work.

25
00:01:57,617 --> 00:01:59,159
Oh, come on.

26
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,788
Just this once. Take a risk.

27
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:03,873
Next time. I promise.

28
00:02:03,874 --> 00:02:05,541
Mm-hm.

29
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:08,627
This is a list of things
that need to be watered.

30
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:10,295
Thursday morning,
don't forget to leave your key

31
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,547
- for Mike and his son for the boiler.
- Right.

32
00:02:12,548 --> 00:02:13,759
Mm.

33
00:02:14,634 --> 00:02:17,261
Uh, those should last
until I get home.

34
00:02:17,262 --> 00:02:18,513
Remind you of me.

35
00:02:20,015 --> 00:02:21,265
Don't need reminding.

36
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:22,432
No?

37
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:23,893
Are you sure
you're gonna be okay?

38
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:25,269
I'll be fine.

39
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:26,437
Come on.

40
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:28,023
Love you.

41
00:02:28,564 --> 00:02:29,899
- Bye.
- Bye.

42
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,400
Bye.

43
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:37,490
- Bye!
- Ooh.

44
00:03:41,637 --> 00:03:43,222
Good to see you, brother.
Yeah. Yeah.

45
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,224
- Uh, oh! What's going on, Chuck?
- Hey.

46
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:47,810
Hey, you, uh--
you just back from somewhere?

47
00:03:47,811 --> 00:03:50,813
Across the pond, man. Everywhere
and nowhere. You know how it is.

48
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:52,564
Yeah. You just buzzin' in
and buzzin' out?

49
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:54,859
Yeah. I got a day
of security debrief...

50
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:57,194
and then,
it's the home base, man.

51
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:59,738
- Go kiss my little girl.
- Oh, that's important.

52
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:01,365
Yeah. I just said
goodbye to my wife.

53
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:02,868
Hey, man, what are you doing
for lunch today?

54
00:04:03,827 --> 00:04:05,119
- Nothin'. No, no plans.
- Yeah?

55
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,496
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm completely free, man.
- That's great.

56
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:08,998
You know,
I got this computer shit.

57
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:10,290
Just a few, like, bits and bytes

58
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:12,960
I would love to get that
big brain of yours to decipher.

59
00:04:12,961 --> 00:04:15,129
I swear, last time, bro,
you saved my life.

60
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:16,463
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

61
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:17,882
- Yeah, of course.
- Oh, that's great. All right.

62
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:20,259
So, uh, you go ahead
and you eat your lunch,

63
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,676
then I'll come get ya?

64
00:04:21,677 --> 00:04:23,262
- Yeah.
- My man.

65
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:24,805
Tick tock, tick boom, bro.

66
00:04:27,558 --> 00:04:29,435
Floor Minus Two. Operations.

67
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:42,240
Floor Minus Five,
Decryption and Analysis.

68
00:05:25,866 --> 00:05:27,492
Hello. Are you there, Charlie?

69
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:30,371
What do you have for me today,
Señor Inquiline?

70
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:34,708
2.1 terabyte tranche.

71
00:05:34,709 --> 00:05:36,085
Kabul Station.

72
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:38,837
2014 to 2022.

73
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:39,839
Open this alone.

74
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:41,799
No charge this time.

75
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:48,514
How's the weather in Istanbul?

76
00:05:49,557 --> 00:05:50,558
Nice try.

77
00:05:51,142 --> 00:05:52,310
It's just a matter of time.

78
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:54,561
You think?

79
00:05:54,562 --> 00:05:57,481
It's been five years, Charlie,
and you're still guessing.

80
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:58,773
I'll get there.

81
00:05:58,774 --> 00:06:00,318
I like puzzles.

82
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:03,445
Not as much as I like anonymity.

83
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:04,821
If I had to guess,
you're a 50-year-old

84
00:06:04,822 --> 00:06:06,573
Russian man
living in Istanbul...

85
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:07,992
with an affinity
for Reddit boards

86
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:10,078
and Turkish coffee.

87
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:12,787
Perhaps, perhaps not.

88
00:06:12,788 --> 00:06:14,956
I'm serious.
Be careful with this data.

89
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:17,626
It's highly compromising
for your agency.

90
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:40,357
Hey.

91
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:41,566
Hi, Team.

92
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:43,985
Tell me again. How big
did you say the crate was?

93
00:06:43,986 --> 00:06:45,820
Twenty meters by 10.

94
00:06:45,821 --> 00:06:48,032
Another one
of Slater's hypotheticals.

95
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:50,909
Satellite images of a crate
on the back of a semi-truck...

96
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:53,745
rectangular in shape,
20 by 10 meters.

97
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:54,913
Destination?

98
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:56,665
A major metropolitan area.

99
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,209
- Mm. LA.
- Wrong coast.

100
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:00,710
Is the truck from Pennsylvania?

101
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:02,671
Mm-hm.

102
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:04,214
Headed to DC?

103
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:05,549
So far, so good.

104
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,758
- A flagpole.
- No, a missile.

105
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,968
Christmas tree.

106
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,638
The White House tree
always comes from a farm

107
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:13,348
in Lehighton, Pennsylvania.

108
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:15,350
And dimensions of the truck
tell the rest.

109
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:16,560
He can be really
annoying sometimes.

110
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:17,478
Wow.

111
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:21,524
Oh, who's that?

112
00:07:21,857 --> 00:07:23,692
The most dangerous
man in the building.

113
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:25,319
Secret agent. Bang, bang.

114
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,528
He and Heller are besties.

115
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:27,696
I'm his bestie.

116
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,740
No. We're just,
uh, acquaintances.

117
00:07:30,241 --> 00:07:31,159
How do you know him?

118
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:33,911
Saved his life.

119
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:50,802
Heller.

120
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:52,180
What are you wearing?

121
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:53,847
Sarah?

122
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:55,600
No. Saddam Hussein.

123
00:07:56,726 --> 00:07:57,560
He's dead.

124
00:07:58,018 --> 00:07:59,269
Humor, Heller.

125
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:00,312
Right, right.

126
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:01,938
I'm just calling
to let you know I'm here.

127
00:08:01,939 --> 00:08:03,690
Right. I know.
I-I know. I tracked you.

128
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:04,899
I'd be hurt if you didn't.

129
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:07,277
I'm just grabbing a coffee.

130
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:08,862
Trying to keep me awake
a little bit longer

131
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:10,364
while I wait
for the rest of the team.

132
00:08:10,365 --> 00:08:12,491
All right. Take a walk.
Go get some fresh air, honey.

133
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:14,243
But I want to lie down.

134
00:08:14,244 --> 00:08:16,035
No. If you lie down,
you'll never get up.

135
00:08:16,036 --> 00:08:19,664
Oh. Is that-- is that sage
advice from the world traveler?

136
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:20,749
Harsh.

137
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,709
Hey, listen.
I'm on to something here.

138
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:23,961
Can I call you later?

139
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:26,588
Yeah. I love you.

140
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:27,839
I love you, babe. Bye. Bye.

141
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,299
- Bye. Bye.
- Bye.

142
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,385
- Bye.
- Bye-bye.

143
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:57,680
What the hell?

144
00:09:59,014 --> 00:10:01,516
There are witness
reports of a drone strike...

145
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:05,604
but U.S. sources have confirmed
that it was a suicide bomber.

146
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:07,231
The scale of the attacks
devastated...

147
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:08,898
Some 150 people killed...

148
00:10:08,899 --> 00:10:11,109
including French special forces.

149
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:13,570
Seven Danish marines were killed
in the explosion...

150
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:16,740
which was initially reported
as a misdirected air strike.

151
00:10:16,741 --> 00:10:18,199
A Department
of Defense spokesman...

152
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:21,202
denied reports of U.S. Air
Force operations in the area...

153
00:10:21,203 --> 00:10:23,205
blaming the attack
on local insurgents.

154
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:25,416
Chief Moore.

155
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:34,675
Hey, buddy.

156
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:36,927
Carlos.

157
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:38,970
You okay?
You look like a damn ghost.

158
00:10:38,971 --> 00:10:41,056
I was just rectifying some...

159
00:10:42,808 --> 00:10:43,683
Charlie?

160
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:44,977
Some files.

161
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:46,479
Okay.

162
00:10:46,937 --> 00:10:48,730
I may have looked somewhere
I shouldn't have.

163
00:10:48,731 --> 00:10:49,981
Within our department?

164
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:51,024
Gray area.

165
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,734
We don't do gray areas, Charlie.

166
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:54,319
Our work is decidedly binary.

167
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,820
Then, no.

168
00:10:55,821 --> 00:10:58,490
In that case,
what you do is you keep quiet.

169
00:10:58,491 --> 00:10:59,409
Yeah.

170
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:15,674
Hey, I'm either busy
or dropped my cell

171
00:11:15,675 --> 00:11:16,883
at the bottom of my bag.

172
00:11:16,884 --> 00:11:18,927
Tell me who you are
and I'll call you back.

173
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:21,220
Hey, it's me.

174
00:11:21,221 --> 00:11:23,223
Um... Miss you.

175
00:11:23,808 --> 00:11:25,935
I will water
the flowers first thing.

176
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:28,646
Call me.

177
00:11:52,127 --> 00:11:53,629
- Chief Moore.
- Charlie.

178
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:58,550
I'm sorry, I don't see you
down here very often, sir.

179
00:11:58,551 --> 00:11:59,510
Why would you?

180
00:12:00,636 --> 00:12:02,345
Nice office you have.

181
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:05,099
Yeah. Yeah, if you don't like
sunlight or fresh air.

182
00:12:06,684 --> 00:12:09,185
For a moss or a lichen
or mushrooms...

183
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:11,271
Charlie, have you been
tracking the news?

184
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:14,191
Well, I'm still tryin' to find
an outlet I can trust.

185
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:15,775
That's what we thought

186
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:17,403
when we heard
you were here this morning.

187
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:19,404
We?

188
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:21,866
I need you to come with me
to the Director's office.

189
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:24,869
Please.

190
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:29,331
Floor Seven. Executive.

191
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:37,047
Director.

192
00:12:41,301 --> 00:12:44,096
Director O'Brien,
this is Charlie Heller.

193
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:46,473
- Hi.
- Hello, Charlie.

194
00:12:46,474 --> 00:12:47,433
Come have a seat.

195
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:48,893
I'd rather not.

196
00:12:51,646 --> 00:12:55,107
Mr. Heller, I'm afraid
there was a situation in London.

197
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,109
Have you heard?

198
00:12:58,193 --> 00:12:59,027
London?

199
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:02,156
An attack at the Christopher Street Hotel.

200
00:13:05,743 --> 00:13:07,077
- Charlie...
- No, no.

201
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:09,663
I'm very sorry, Mr. Heller.

202
00:13:09,664 --> 00:13:11,247
What?

203
00:13:11,248 --> 00:13:13,208
- Your wife has been killed.
- No.

204
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:15,001
No, she's at a conference.

205
00:13:15,002 --> 00:13:16,085
We should call her.

206
00:13:16,086 --> 00:13:17,462
Charlie, I'm very sorry
to give you this...

207
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:19,131
Can we call her?
I have to call her.

208
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:21,509
Charlie, I think
you need to see this.

209
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:24,343
We're following
a breaking news story

210
00:13:24,344 --> 00:13:25,887
here in London...

211
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:29,057
where a terrifying hostage
situation unfolded...

212
00:13:29,058 --> 00:13:32,060
at the Christopher Street Hotel
earlier today.

213
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:34,854
Four assailants
stormed into the hotel,

214
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:37,816
taking a number
of individuals hostage.

215
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:41,402
Two individuals
sadly lost their lives...

216
00:13:41,403 --> 00:13:44,155
including an American woman
who was taken hostage...

217
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:46,575
- It doesn't say it's her.
- ...during the ordeal.

218
00:13:46,576 --> 00:13:47,492
Eyewitnesses report...

219
00:13:47,493 --> 00:13:48,827
Charlie, you have
to believe us.

220
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:50,119
...a chaotic scene
inside the hotel

221
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,955
as the perpetrators
forced their way...

222
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:54,916
This is footage we pulled
from surveillance cams.

223
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:57,210
...terrorized the guests
and the staff.

224
00:13:57,211 --> 00:13:59,754
One of the victims
has been identified.

225
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:02,173
She is a 32-year-old
American woman...

226
00:14:02,174 --> 00:14:05,051
that was tragically
taken hostage by the assailants.

227
00:14:05,052 --> 00:14:06,720
The police are
not revealing her.

228
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:29,659
It's all right.

229
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:31,203
I got this.
Don't worry about it.

230
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:34,749
Charlie, Charlie, wait!

231
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:39,502
Charles! Charles!

232
00:14:42,006 --> 00:14:43,840
Metropolitan
Police has initiated

233
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:46,009
a citywide manhunt.

234
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:48,136
They are working tirelessly
to locate the assailants...

235
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:51,723
...and secure
the rescue and release...

236
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,644
...of the-- the hostage...

237
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,760
How can we not know more?

238
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:30,596
This was in London...

239
00:15:30,971 --> 00:15:34,182
947,000 cameras.

240
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,100
They drove into traffic.

241
00:15:36,101 --> 00:15:38,019
Nobody is getting
away with this.

242
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,478
You have my word.

243
00:15:39,479 --> 00:15:40,773
Okay.

244
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,318
Tell me what we know so far.

245
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:46,945
Mr. Heller...

246
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:50,282
with respect,
let us handle this.

247
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,951
Forgive me, sir, I don't believe
we've officially met.

248
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,619
I'm the one who's gonna ensure
that those who did this

249
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:57,246
are held to account.

250
00:15:57,247 --> 00:16:00,125
And what would that look like,
sir, with respect...

251
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:03,336
being "held to account"?

252
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:06,215
Look, we can't get
into specifics yet.

253
00:16:07,341 --> 00:16:09,301
Of course, you understand that.

254
00:16:09,802 --> 00:16:13,513
We'll tell you what we can
as soon as we can.

255
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:16,182
You just said
what he said, only nicer.

256
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:18,101
Go home, Charlie.

257
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:20,187
You need to take some time.

258
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:18,662
- Next of kin?
- Yes.

259
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:48,519
The suspects arrived
via the service entrance

260
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,313
around 11:00 hours.

261
00:19:50,314 --> 00:19:52,315
The vehicle had been
stolen overnight

262
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:55,109
at about 01:24 in the East End.

263
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:57,821
Prints, DNA,
all professionally scrubbed out.

264
00:19:58,197 --> 00:19:59,989
Four-person team.

265
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:01,365
Appears they had a meeting...

266
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:04,452
with Impact Investments
out of Indonesia on our radar.

267
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:06,080
This is when it all started.

268
00:20:06,621 --> 00:20:08,622
Something must have
got heated inside,

269
00:20:08,623 --> 00:20:10,624
it spilled out
into the corridor.

270
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:12,794
Impact's security
detail got jumpy,

271
00:20:13,087 --> 00:20:14,463
and one of the four drew on him.

272
00:20:15,172 --> 00:20:16,881
One dead, one critical.

273
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:19,593
Hotel security are alerted,
and the police have been called.

274
00:20:20,719 --> 00:20:22,887
The suspects are now in a race
to leave the building...

275
00:20:23,722 --> 00:20:25,681
and they decided
to grab some insurance.

276
00:20:29,019 --> 00:20:30,603
Everyone! Get down!

277
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:33,983
Everyone down.

278
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,322
Get down. Get down.

279
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:42,656
No, no, no. Run. Run.

280
00:20:42,657 --> 00:20:44,617
They only took Sarah
because she tried

281
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:45,868
to save someone else.

282
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:52,875
You do as I say. Move!

283
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:55,504
You do as I say. Move!

284
00:20:57,797 --> 00:20:59,633
You do as I say. Move!

285
00:21:00,884 --> 00:21:03,677
The man who took Sarah
is Mishka Blazhic.

286
00:21:03,678 --> 00:21:06,472
Origins in Belarus,
though often based in Moscow.

287
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,893
They fled the conference room
with three hostages.

288
00:21:11,811 --> 00:21:15,939
Stay down,
or I'll shoot you!

289
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,652
This man, Lawrence
Ellish, is South African.

290
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:21,320
Ex-special forces.

291
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:23,865
Ellish seems to handle shipments
for the wider group.

292
00:21:24,449 --> 00:21:26,284
Armed police
and security were arriving

293
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:27,618
from St. Pancras Station,

294
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:30,622
but were ordered to hold back
because of the hostages.

295
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:35,834
Police sealed off the area,
marksmen in position,

296
00:21:35,835 --> 00:21:38,921
but the suspects are exposed,
and they knew it.

297
00:21:40,049 --> 00:21:41,382
Armed police!
Drop your weapons!

298
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:42,342
Get down!

299
00:21:43,052 --> 00:21:45,554
Let go of me! No!

300
00:21:58,275 --> 00:22:00,943
Sarah's killer
is harder to track.

301
00:22:00,944 --> 00:22:03,988
He seems to sense the cameras.
He says nothing.

302
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:07,283
But I processed all the CCTV,
cell phones...

303
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:08,951
dash cams, body cams...

304
00:22:08,952 --> 00:22:11,037
and the audio to give us a 360.

305
00:22:11,705 --> 00:22:13,457
And that provides us with an ID.

306
00:22:14,374 --> 00:22:15,999
This is Horst Schiller.

307
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:19,170
Loose affiliations with dozens
of mercs and defense groups.

308
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:20,879
I'm still filling that in.

309
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,923
They seem to be
operating as interface

310
00:22:22,924 --> 00:22:26,009
between bad state actors
and terrorist entities.

311
00:22:26,010 --> 00:22:27,429
All business.

312
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:29,389
And they keep getting hired.

313
00:22:30,265 --> 00:22:32,516
But for this one,
I have a current location.

314
00:22:32,517 --> 00:22:34,185
Gretchen Frank.

315
00:22:34,186 --> 00:22:36,313
Former Armenian IO.

316
00:22:36,605 --> 00:22:37,939
She's in Paris.

317
00:22:38,898 --> 00:22:40,775
Buys her bread at this cafe.

318
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:42,944
Turns up there regularly.

319
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:52,537
You knew this?

320
00:22:52,912 --> 00:22:53,913
Thank you.

321
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:56,708
- We'll do a comparison.
- Wait.

322
00:22:57,626 --> 00:22:59,418
You already know
about Gretchen Frank?

323
00:22:59,419 --> 00:23:02,464
I understand you
wanna see progress, Charlie.

324
00:23:03,298 --> 00:23:05,717
But sometimes,
the best course of action...

325
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,094
isn't always the most obvious.

326
00:23:08,345 --> 00:23:09,178
"Most obvious"?

327
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:11,096
We want the whole network.

328
00:23:11,097 --> 00:23:13,015
The network has nothing
to do with Sarah.

329
00:23:13,016 --> 00:23:16,059
But everything to do
with the sovereignty

330
00:23:16,060 --> 00:23:17,229
and security of this country.

331
00:23:17,937 --> 00:23:23,318
What you do is very important
to what we do, Charlie.

332
00:23:24,486 --> 00:23:27,572
We think it would be good
for you to see Dr. Garrison.

333
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:36,415
Am I here for me or the Agency?

334
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:41,084
It is important we assess you're
well enough to return to work.

335
00:23:41,085 --> 00:23:42,296
- Mm.
- Obviously.

336
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:46,132
But you've suffered
a terrible loss.

337
00:23:46,966 --> 00:23:48,677
And we want to support you.

338
00:23:50,762 --> 00:23:53,223
Can you describe your feelings?

339
00:23:54,140 --> 00:23:55,141
Right now?

340
00:23:55,684 --> 00:23:58,101
You mean, denial, anger...

341
00:23:58,102 --> 00:23:59,354
acceptance...

342
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,691
Say more.

343
00:24:05,985 --> 00:24:07,196
She's gone.

344
00:24:12,992 --> 00:24:14,578
Yeah, that she had
to go like that.

345
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:28,091
And that I didn't speak to her
on the phone when she called.

346
00:24:30,134 --> 00:24:31,510
And you blame
yourself for that?

347
00:24:31,511 --> 00:24:32,512
Yes.

348
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,767
For not going with her
when she asked me to,

349
00:24:38,768 --> 00:24:40,270
because I never do.

350
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:43,982
Never did.

351
00:24:49,112 --> 00:24:50,697
And what is that
making you feel?

352
00:24:55,327 --> 00:24:56,661
Uh, pretty useless.

353
00:24:58,413 --> 00:24:59,748
A-Angry.

354
00:25:02,041 --> 00:25:03,668
Very, very angry.

355
00:25:09,591 --> 00:25:14,219
Uh, I gave the Agency
the names of Sarah's killers.

356
00:25:14,220 --> 00:25:15,514
They did nothing.

357
00:25:16,598 --> 00:25:18,558
- What do you want them to do?
- Their job!

358
00:25:20,018 --> 00:25:22,228
I want them to go
after Sarah's killers.

359
00:25:24,439 --> 00:25:26,024
Will that make you feel better?

360
00:25:27,108 --> 00:25:28,859
This shouldn't be about me.

361
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:30,320
Sarah mattered.

362
00:25:32,322 --> 00:25:33,823
She deserves more.

363
00:25:35,241 --> 00:25:37,661
But in the end,
this is about you.

364
00:25:39,871 --> 00:25:40,872
Sarah's gone.

365
00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:45,877
You are gonna have to try
and come to terms with that.

366
00:25:48,588 --> 00:25:50,214
I can help.

367
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:53,802
But only you can really
make things better.

368
00:26:18,493 --> 00:26:19,827
Floor Minus Five.

369
00:26:19,828 --> 00:26:21,537
Decryption and Analysis.

370
00:26:30,464 --> 00:26:31,880
And the renovation schedule?

371
00:26:31,881 --> 00:26:33,257
We can discuss
the cryptography project.

372
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:49,231
Okay. All right. I can do this.

373
00:26:49,232 --> 00:26:51,443
Thanks.
I think we need to flag this.

374
00:27:19,929 --> 00:27:21,305
You've been very quiet lately.

375
00:27:21,931 --> 00:27:23,475
Guessed where I live yet?

376
00:27:43,411 --> 00:27:45,328
You good here
for a minute, buddy?

377
00:27:45,329 --> 00:27:46,914
I gotta close up the back.

378
00:27:46,915 --> 00:27:48,458
Oh, yeah. Yeah. I--

379
00:27:49,042 --> 00:27:50,251
I got you covered out here.

380
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:09,813
Floor Seven. Executive.

381
00:28:22,909 --> 00:28:26,580
I'm holding the highlights
of over 100 eyes-only cables.

382
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:28,371
These are double coded
from a data cache

383
00:28:28,372 --> 00:28:29,748
out of Kabul Station.

384
00:28:29,749 --> 00:28:31,250
These are the official cables.

385
00:28:31,626 --> 00:28:33,919
Same dates, same events,

386
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:37,715
except for very key information
that has been altered

387
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:40,594
or completely scrubbed
from the record.

388
00:28:41,511 --> 00:28:42,846
What are you talking about?

389
00:28:46,182 --> 00:28:47,350
This is your cover-up.

390
00:28:47,809 --> 00:28:48,851
Have you lost your mind?

391
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:50,102
To put it mildly.

392
00:28:50,103 --> 00:28:55,065
This is your order of operations
to destroy a hospital in Syria.

393
00:28:55,066 --> 00:28:57,359
An allied base in Yemen.

394
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:59,027
An Afghani politician's house.

395
00:28:59,028 --> 00:29:00,195
You have no idea what...

396
00:29:00,196 --> 00:29:01,614
A border crossing in Somalia.

397
00:29:01,615 --> 00:29:04,074
I count more
than 1,000 casualties

398
00:29:04,075 --> 00:29:07,035
and over 400
civilian fatalities.

399
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:09,705
It's only out of respect
for your recent loss

400
00:29:09,706 --> 00:29:12,082
that I'm not throwing you
out of this office.

401
00:29:12,083 --> 00:29:15,460
I'm just gonna tell you,
you don't have a goddamn clue.

402
00:29:15,461 --> 00:29:16,545
You see right here?

403
00:29:16,546 --> 00:29:17,922
The convoy?

404
00:29:19,007 --> 00:29:20,383
You targeted our allies.

405
00:29:21,425 --> 00:29:22,509
You false-flagged it.

406
00:29:22,510 --> 00:29:24,219
You got them all fired up

407
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,387
and then sucked them
right back in

408
00:29:25,388 --> 00:29:26,765
where you wanted them.

409
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:28,515
You were forcing mission creep.

410
00:29:28,516 --> 00:29:30,059
Okay. That's enough.

411
00:29:31,477 --> 00:29:32,520
"That's enough"?

412
00:29:33,146 --> 00:29:35,148
These were not
operational choices.

413
00:29:36,399 --> 00:29:39,152
You, sir, made
political decisions.

414
00:29:40,194 --> 00:29:42,571
And your signatures
are all over these.

415
00:29:42,572 --> 00:29:45,240
Here and-- and here.
And here. Here.

416
00:29:45,241 --> 00:29:47,951
You are so far
above your pay grade.

417
00:29:47,952 --> 00:29:49,745
Well, you're right.
You're right.

418
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:51,039
Maybe we should...

419
00:29:51,706 --> 00:29:53,332
take this up with the director?

420
00:29:55,293 --> 00:29:56,334
Let her call it?

421
00:29:56,335 --> 00:29:57,336
Or...

422
00:29:58,046 --> 00:30:00,338
maybe it's for--
for the Times or the Post.

423
00:30:00,339 --> 00:30:01,882
You've been
to the press with this?

424
00:30:01,883 --> 00:30:03,216
You'll go to jail, idiot.

425
00:30:03,217 --> 00:30:06,053
Maybe.
But we'll all be there together.

426
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:07,971
- We have a mission here.
- Uh-huh.

427
00:30:07,972 --> 00:30:09,307
A responsibility.

428
00:30:09,641 --> 00:30:12,560
We'll defend our nation
by any means necessary.

429
00:30:13,019 --> 00:30:14,770
I don't think
Mr. Heller came here

430
00:30:14,771 --> 00:30:18,148
to debate ethics
and practices, right?

431
00:30:18,149 --> 00:30:19,233
Right.

432
00:30:21,277 --> 00:30:23,779
First, you need to know that
I've set up a dead man's switch.

433
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:25,530
If I don't code in
every five hours,

434
00:30:25,531 --> 00:30:27,574
these files will
automatically be sent

435
00:30:27,575 --> 00:30:29,868
to three top
investigative journalists,

436
00:30:29,869 --> 00:30:32,705
along with a detailed report
and timeline of the events.

437
00:30:32,706 --> 00:30:34,206
Twenty-four hours later,

438
00:30:34,207 --> 00:30:36,458
the files will be
released to the public.

439
00:30:36,459 --> 00:30:37,626
I get it.

440
00:30:37,627 --> 00:30:40,295
We kill you,
Wolf Blitzer wins an Emmy.

441
00:30:40,296 --> 00:30:41,504
No. Not just kill me.

442
00:30:41,505 --> 00:30:42,422
You put me in jail,

443
00:30:42,423 --> 00:30:44,382
you black-site me,
you extradite me...

444
00:30:44,383 --> 00:30:46,051
you'll only condemn yourselves.

445
00:30:46,052 --> 00:30:47,803
Then what the hell do you want?

446
00:30:47,804 --> 00:30:50,097
He wants us to kill the people
who killed his wife.

447
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:51,683
No. No.

448
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:54,143
I don't want you to kill them.

449
00:30:56,229 --> 00:30:58,189
I wanna kill them myself.

450
00:31:01,109 --> 00:31:02,777
- I beg your pardon?
- You heard me.

451
00:31:03,527 --> 00:31:05,612
I want to find and kill
the people who murdered my wife.

452
00:31:07,573 --> 00:31:08,782
The CIA will train me.

453
00:31:10,576 --> 00:31:13,495
I mean, this is
a practical joke, right?

454
00:31:13,496 --> 00:31:15,789
I don't think you could beat
a 90-year-old nun

455
00:31:15,790 --> 00:31:17,124
in an arm-wrestling match.

456
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:18,542
That's funny.

457
00:31:19,502 --> 00:31:20,419
Humor?

458
00:31:21,295 --> 00:31:22,963
I want
mission-specific training

459
00:31:22,964 --> 00:31:25,673
and all the information
the company has on these people.

460
00:31:25,674 --> 00:31:27,886
Cash. And a new identity.
A legend.

461
00:31:29,137 --> 00:31:31,471
Anything else?

462
00:31:31,472 --> 00:31:33,266
An Aston Martin?

463
00:31:33,767 --> 00:31:35,308
A jet pack, maybe?

464
00:31:38,187 --> 00:31:39,856
I want a fighting chance.

465
00:32:09,552 --> 00:32:11,428
How do we know he really set up
the dead man's switch?

466
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:12,595
We don't.

467
00:32:12,596 --> 00:32:14,514
We need to keep a lid on this.

468
00:32:14,515 --> 00:32:15,641
Right.

469
00:32:16,851 --> 00:32:18,102
So, let's play along...

470
00:32:19,353 --> 00:32:20,604
till we're sure.

471
00:32:22,023 --> 00:32:23,941
What? Actually train him?

472
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:25,483
What harm can it do?

473
00:32:25,484 --> 00:32:27,652
Probably quit of his own accord.

474
00:32:27,653 --> 00:32:29,613
Meanwhile, get Park onto him.

475
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:31,614
I can't believe I'm doing this.

476
00:32:31,615 --> 00:32:35,577
We scrub his life
till we find the switch.

477
00:32:35,578 --> 00:32:37,079
If it exists.

478
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:38,663
If it doesn't...

479
00:32:38,664 --> 00:32:41,584
well, maybe there's
a training accident.

480
00:32:44,253 --> 00:32:45,922
Let's use Henderson.

481
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:49,050
Escort team, stand by
for new arrival at gate four.

482
00:32:54,555 --> 00:32:55,556
Charles Heller?

483
00:32:56,724 --> 00:32:57,558
Charlie.

484
00:32:58,434 --> 00:32:59,518
You're late.

485
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,396
With respect,
I'm actually about--

486
00:33:03,397 --> 00:33:04,941
You're late.

487
00:33:06,901 --> 00:33:07,902
You comin'?

488
00:33:14,700 --> 00:33:15,743
The hell you doin'?

489
00:33:16,535 --> 00:33:17,745
I'm not an Uber driver.

490
00:33:18,496 --> 00:33:19,455
Sorry.

491
00:33:25,669 --> 00:33:27,338
- Okay.
- Put it over here on the left.

492
00:33:28,047 --> 00:33:29,381
Yeah. Put those
two routers over there.

493
00:33:29,382 --> 00:33:30,298
I got 'em.

494
00:33:30,299 --> 00:33:31,383
The HDMI cables
are in the box.

495
00:33:31,384 --> 00:33:33,010
My bet is he's bluffing.

496
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:36,097
The man has an IQ of 170.
Let's not assume.

497
00:33:36,722 --> 00:33:38,390
The only way out
is through security...

498
00:33:38,391 --> 00:33:40,977
and there's not a chance he got
past them with a digital file.

499
00:33:42,436 --> 00:33:45,022
Then why is he standing in
blind spots for over 40 minutes?

500
00:33:45,023 --> 00:33:47,358
Here, here, and here.
On this day.

501
00:33:50,444 --> 00:33:52,779
And look at that sweat.

502
00:33:52,780 --> 00:33:56,200
Yeah. That is a lot of sweat.

503
00:34:00,621 --> 00:34:01,705
Are you my...

504
00:34:02,706 --> 00:34:03,749
...handler?

505
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:06,085
I am Colonel Henderson.

506
00:34:07,045 --> 00:34:08,586
My friends call me Hendo.

507
00:34:08,587 --> 00:34:11,090
You will call me
Colonel Henderson.

508
00:34:11,966 --> 00:34:14,384
I have been asked to give you
a refresher course,

509
00:34:14,385 --> 00:34:16,011
even though
what you'll learn here

510
00:34:16,012 --> 00:34:18,346
is outside
the normal curriculum.

511
00:34:18,347 --> 00:34:19,389
Next to God Almighty,

512
00:34:19,390 --> 00:34:21,391
I am the most important
person in the world

513
00:34:21,392 --> 00:34:23,936
to an operative looking
to target enemy combatants.

514
00:34:23,937 --> 00:34:25,313
Do precisely as I say...

515
00:34:25,897 --> 00:34:29,067
and there is a slight chance
you may come out of this alive.

516
00:34:31,945 --> 00:34:33,361
O-Only a slight chance?

517
00:34:33,362 --> 00:34:36,157
I'm overestimating your odds
to boost your confidence, son.

518
00:34:39,118 --> 00:34:42,455
Ladies and gentlemen,
please give us the room.

519
00:34:43,164 --> 00:34:45,332
Go have coffee. Now.

520
00:34:51,923 --> 00:34:53,506
Yeah, make sure
you check for all spots.

521
00:34:53,507 --> 00:34:54,800
All right, checking.

522
00:34:58,471 --> 00:35:00,056
Open all hard drive cleaners.

523
00:35:01,182 --> 00:35:02,515
Bring the mountings too.

524
00:35:02,516 --> 00:35:04,059
Wait. You think
he used a skimmer?

525
00:35:04,060 --> 00:35:05,728
They don't work on these drives.

526
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:08,106
They work on printers.

527
00:35:09,273 --> 00:35:11,399
Six days ago, he sent
the files to the printer...

528
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,486
and skimmed them
with a magnetic strip...

529
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:15,738
rewrote the software
in the printer.

530
00:35:16,239 --> 00:35:18,116
Doesn't mean he got
the strip out of the building.

531
00:35:19,492 --> 00:35:24,621
Okay. So, ANPR has his Saab at
Best Buy at 09:17 on the 13th,

532
00:35:24,622 --> 00:35:26,456
where he bought
the magnetic strip.

533
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:27,540
Then got gas.

534
00:35:27,541 --> 00:35:30,043
Copied the files at 11:03...

535
00:35:30,044 --> 00:35:32,129
met you two the next morning.

536
00:35:32,130 --> 00:35:36,424
If he smuggled it out,
he did it here.

537
00:35:36,425 --> 00:35:38,468
Still, screener
picked up nothing.

538
00:35:38,469 --> 00:35:39,720
Maybe he swallowed it.

539
00:35:40,013 --> 00:35:41,514
Still would have picked it up.

540
00:35:54,943 --> 00:35:55,986
Kind of far.

541
00:35:58,697 --> 00:35:59,865
You stand right there.

542
00:36:09,083 --> 00:36:10,917
Hold your fire!

543
00:36:10,918 --> 00:36:12,377
Try it closer.

544
00:36:12,378 --> 00:36:13,712
Just a few rounds.

545
00:36:24,182 --> 00:36:25,848
Jesus, Mary, and Joseph.

546
00:36:25,849 --> 00:36:27,393
Did we test your vision?

547
00:36:42,366 --> 00:36:44,077
Guess I just have
to get that close.

548
00:36:44,702 --> 00:36:46,495
Yeah, at point blank range...

549
00:36:47,413 --> 00:36:49,873
you might have a 50-50 chance
of hittin' something.

550
00:36:50,583 --> 00:36:52,668
Overestimating my odds?

551
00:37:02,136 --> 00:37:04,137
Why don't you guys check
the downstairs bathroom?

552
00:37:04,138 --> 00:37:05,347
Pass me those boxes.

553
00:37:09,893 --> 00:37:12,563
So, an IED consists
of an initiator...

554
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:15,107
switch, main charge,

555
00:37:15,108 --> 00:37:17,525
power source,
container for enhancements.

556
00:37:17,526 --> 00:37:19,611
Stuff like fertilizer, nails,

557
00:37:19,612 --> 00:37:21,904
glass, ammonia nitrate.

558
00:37:21,905 --> 00:37:23,865
Beauty is,
you can use what you find,

559
00:37:23,866 --> 00:37:25,408
big or small, as you like.

560
00:37:25,409 --> 00:37:27,411
Improvise.
Design it for your purpose.

561
00:37:27,745 --> 00:37:29,497
Carry the components with you.

562
00:37:30,539 --> 00:37:32,207
I'll be damned.

563
00:37:32,208 --> 00:37:34,752
Looks like we finally found
something you do well, Heller.

564
00:37:41,425 --> 00:37:42,676
May I keep this?

565
00:37:43,511 --> 00:37:44,886
Sure.

566
00:37:44,887 --> 00:37:47,805
He went here twice. This bar.

567
00:37:47,806 --> 00:37:48,723
Why?

568
00:37:48,724 --> 00:37:51,768
Once with Mr. Dominguez
on the night of the 24th.

569
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:53,520
Couple of weeks
after his wife died.

570
00:37:53,521 --> 00:37:55,438
And then again,
the next month, the 13th.

571
00:37:55,439 --> 00:37:56,898
The day he downloaded the files.

572
00:37:56,899 --> 00:37:57,982
Right.

573
00:37:57,983 --> 00:37:59,442
We searched it, though.

574
00:37:59,443 --> 00:38:00,360
Let's search it again.

575
00:38:00,361 --> 00:38:02,445
- Name?
- Clark Nicholas Jenson.

576
00:38:02,446 --> 00:38:03,530
Spell that for me.

577
00:38:03,531 --> 00:38:05,198
J-E-N-S-O-N.

578
00:38:05,199 --> 00:38:06,115
- You sure?
- Yeah.

579
00:38:06,116 --> 00:38:07,325
Not Jenson Clark?

580
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:08,618
- No!
- Fast.

581
00:38:08,619 --> 00:38:10,537
- Clark Nicholas Jenson.
- Where were you born?

582
00:38:10,538 --> 00:38:11,788
Raleigh.
Raleigh, North Carolina.

583
00:38:11,789 --> 00:38:14,249
- Which hospital? Now!
- Uh, Duke University Hospital.

584
00:38:14,250 --> 00:38:16,668
- Your mother's maiden name?
- Uh, Deborah Jane Hammock.

585
00:38:19,797 --> 00:38:20,631
Just a sec.

586
00:38:27,888 --> 00:38:30,223
It's all being re-swept.
Even the parking lot.

587
00:38:30,224 --> 00:38:31,642
There's no drive here.

588
00:38:31,934 --> 00:38:33,601
Okay. That's what
we didn't find.

589
00:38:33,602 --> 00:38:35,145
But what did we find?

590
00:38:36,189 --> 00:38:39,567
I don't know, this was
stuck under the jukebox.

591
00:38:43,571 --> 00:38:45,030
Give me a quarter.

592
00:38:58,627 --> 00:38:59,753
Pull the disc.

593
00:39:08,929 --> 00:39:10,013
You...

594
00:39:10,889 --> 00:39:11,974
are not a killer.

595
00:39:14,142 --> 00:39:14,977
No?

596
00:39:15,311 --> 00:39:16,979
- Hey, who's this?
- Leave them.

597
00:39:17,938 --> 00:39:19,815
Oh, these the assholes
that killed your wife, huh?

598
00:39:21,359 --> 00:39:24,361
So, how do you plan
to take them all out?

599
00:39:24,362 --> 00:39:25,695
The first one you kill,

600
00:39:25,696 --> 00:39:27,113
you let the other ones
know you're coming.

601
00:39:27,114 --> 00:39:28,699
And then what? What's your plan?

602
00:39:28,991 --> 00:39:29,824
How are you gonna keep

603
00:39:29,825 --> 00:39:31,410
the people
at Langley off your ass?

604
00:39:32,995 --> 00:39:34,704
That's what I need
you to teach me.

605
00:39:36,206 --> 00:39:37,500
All right. I'll teach you.

606
00:39:40,794 --> 00:39:41,878
Take it.

607
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:42,837
- Oh, come on.
- Go on, take it.

608
00:39:42,838 --> 00:39:43,755
What is it? What are you...

609
00:39:43,756 --> 00:39:45,258
- Take it! Now!
- Hey!

610
00:39:47,468 --> 00:39:48,469
Point it at my chest.

611
00:39:49,512 --> 00:39:50,803
- Point it at my chest!
- You think that...

612
00:39:50,804 --> 00:39:53,222
- Do it now!
- All right, all right.

613
00:39:53,223 --> 00:39:55,309
Put your finger on the trigger!

614
00:39:57,102 --> 00:39:58,395
Come on.

615
00:39:58,396 --> 00:39:59,480
Look at me.

616
00:40:03,776 --> 00:40:04,652
Come on.

617
00:40:05,444 --> 00:40:07,321
Come on, Charlie.

618
00:40:18,248 --> 00:40:19,542
Paralyzing, isn't it?

619
00:40:21,209 --> 00:40:23,337
Pointing a live weapon
at someone like that.

620
00:40:26,006 --> 00:40:28,425
You have to either be
very confident or very stupid,

621
00:40:28,426 --> 00:40:30,636
which is its own
kind of confidence.

622
00:40:30,928 --> 00:40:32,887
Truth is you don't have
that kinda confidence.

623
00:40:32,888 --> 00:40:35,807
And you are not stupid.
Not in the slightest.

624
00:40:35,808 --> 00:40:37,476
You're just not a killer,
Charlie.

625
00:40:38,852 --> 00:40:40,270
People have certain gifts.

626
00:40:41,730 --> 00:40:44,483
You can't do what I do, no
matter how much I train you...

627
00:40:45,318 --> 00:40:48,319
as much as you can't teach me
how to break code.

628
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:50,614
I can't make you into somethin'
that you're not.

629
00:40:51,239 --> 00:40:52,450
I'm sorry.

630
00:40:54,410 --> 00:40:55,911
When the time comes...

631
00:40:56,954 --> 00:40:58,538
I'll pull--
I'll pull the trigger.

632
00:40:58,539 --> 00:41:00,165
When the time comes...

633
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:02,166
you won't even remember
which end of the gun

634
00:41:02,167 --> 00:41:03,669
the bullet comes out of.

635
00:41:12,010 --> 00:41:13,345
How long is this gonna take?

636
00:41:14,763 --> 00:41:17,224
With this encryption,
four or five hours.

637
00:41:22,145 --> 00:41:24,689
What if she
can't break Heller's encryption?

638
00:41:24,690 --> 00:41:25,816
She will.

639
00:41:26,692 --> 00:41:28,861
How do we know
he didn't make 50 copies?

640
00:41:29,528 --> 00:41:31,238
We don't.

641
00:41:37,620 --> 00:41:38,536
Ali.

642
00:41:38,537 --> 00:41:39,746
We're in.

643
00:41:39,747 --> 00:41:41,039
It's a bluff.

644
00:41:41,331 --> 00:41:42,624
He was playing us.

645
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:44,376
And he did pretty well, too.

646
00:41:45,669 --> 00:41:46,670
Take him off the board?

647
00:41:55,971 --> 00:41:56,972
Yeah.

648
00:42:03,979 --> 00:42:04,938
Okay.

649
00:42:20,454 --> 00:42:21,788
He's gone?

650
00:42:21,789 --> 00:42:23,289
He's got a bag
full of passports.

651
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,082
Even hacked the biometrics.

652
00:42:25,083 --> 00:42:26,668
Yeah, he got out
on a janitor's card.

653
00:42:26,669 --> 00:42:28,170
This is a joke.

654
00:42:28,796 --> 00:42:30,421
Maybe y'all misjudged
this individual.

655
00:42:30,422 --> 00:42:31,423
You think?

656
00:42:34,677 --> 00:42:36,845
He knew exactly
what he was doin'.

657
00:42:37,721 --> 00:42:40,098
Kept us chasin' breadcrumbs
just long enough...

658
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:42,309
while he got himself
some training.

659
00:43:17,886 --> 00:43:18,929
Mr. Heller...

660
00:43:20,806 --> 00:43:22,975
bugging a CIA officer...

661
00:43:23,851 --> 00:43:24,934
is treason.

662
00:43:24,935 --> 00:43:28,981
Call for flight AA143
to London Heathrow.

663
00:43:37,405 --> 00:43:39,281
Ladies
and gentlemen, welcome aboard

664
00:43:39,282 --> 00:43:42,201
American Airlines flight AA143,

665
00:43:42,202 --> 00:43:43,870
with service
from Washington Dulles

666
00:43:43,871 --> 00:43:45,497
to London Heathrow.

667
00:43:46,206 --> 00:43:48,457
We thank you for your attention
whilst we demonstrate

668
00:43:48,458 --> 00:43:51,294
the safety features
of the aircraft.

669
00:43:56,091 --> 00:43:57,049
Yes?

670
00:43:57,050 --> 00:43:59,011
Okay, you can open them.

671
00:44:03,599 --> 00:44:05,142
Happy birthday.

672
00:44:10,397 --> 00:44:11,731
Did it-- did it crash?

673
00:44:11,732 --> 00:44:14,066
Apparently it wasn't
tied down properly

674
00:44:14,067 --> 00:44:16,485
and got thrown around
in a tornado

675
00:44:16,486 --> 00:44:18,404
or hurricane or something.

676
00:44:20,323 --> 00:44:21,449
What do you think?

677
00:44:22,534 --> 00:44:24,578
I have no words.

678
00:44:25,495 --> 00:44:27,288
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

679
00:44:27,289 --> 00:44:28,540
It's not crazy?

680
00:44:33,295 --> 00:44:34,880
It needs some work.

681
00:44:36,339 --> 00:44:37,299
You think?

682
00:44:42,262 --> 00:44:43,180
This...

683
00:44:44,056 --> 00:44:46,558
This is the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

684
00:44:47,893 --> 00:44:48,976
Yeah?

685
00:44:48,977 --> 00:44:50,312
Yeah.

686
00:44:51,271 --> 00:44:52,648
Second most.

687
00:44:56,151 --> 00:44:57,235
Happy birthday.

688
00:45:02,991 --> 00:45:06,036
...Paris will be departing now
from platform two.

689
00:45:14,837 --> 00:45:15,920
He's in London.

690
00:45:15,921 --> 00:45:17,964
One of his passports
just lit up at immigration

691
00:45:17,965 --> 00:45:19,924
on his way to Paris.

692
00:45:19,925 --> 00:45:22,176
- I'll grab local liaison.
- No.

693
00:45:22,177 --> 00:45:23,721
This stays with us.

694
00:45:24,471 --> 00:45:25,597
What about Henderson?

695
00:45:27,557 --> 00:45:28,976
Call him.

696
00:46:16,689 --> 00:46:18,400
Non, vraiment,
vous êtes déjà fermés ?

697
00:47:41,817 --> 00:47:43,275
Hey, there, lockpick fans.

698
00:47:43,276 --> 00:47:46,487
Okay. Today we're gonna pick
an apartment-style lock.

699
00:47:46,488 --> 00:47:48,239
So, the first thing
we're gonna do

700
00:47:48,240 --> 00:47:49,740
is you're gonna take
your tension wrench

701
00:47:49,741 --> 00:47:51,450
and you're gonna
stick it in the bottom

702
00:47:51,451 --> 00:47:53,160
of the keyhole and the plug...

703
00:47:53,161 --> 00:47:54,829
just like so. Feel it?

704
00:47:56,039 --> 00:47:57,748
You're gonna apply just
a little bit of pressure,

705
00:47:57,749 --> 00:47:59,125
just a little bit.

706
00:47:59,126 --> 00:48:00,501
Hey, you don't want too much.

707
00:48:00,502 --> 00:48:02,044
Too much,
and what's gonna happen

708
00:48:02,045 --> 00:48:03,880
is the pins are gonna
bind up on you...

709
00:48:03,881 --> 00:48:06,132
and you won't be able to get 'em
up on a shear line.

710
00:48:06,133 --> 00:48:08,759
And you're not gonna
get into that door.

711
00:48:08,760 --> 00:48:12,429
So, gently, gently...

712
00:48:12,430 --> 00:48:16,475
and feel it rotate back and
forwards, listening carefully.

713
00:48:16,476 --> 00:48:18,102
Just a light touch.

714
00:48:18,103 --> 00:48:21,022
All the pins are gonna line up.

715
00:48:21,023 --> 00:48:24,275
And then, you're in.
There you go.

716
00:48:24,276 --> 00:48:25,567
How to pick a lock.

717
00:48:25,568 --> 00:48:26,736
Pretty darn easy.

718
00:48:27,195 --> 00:48:29,155
Um... Yeah, don't forget
to like and subscribe.

719
00:48:29,156 --> 00:48:30,532
Thank y'all. See you next week.

720
00:49:32,010 --> 00:49:35,305
Moi, j'oublie tout.
Bon, je te prête mes talons...

721
00:49:45,315 --> 00:49:48,276
T'as oublié le pain.

722
00:49:49,236 --> 00:49:51,238
La boulangerie était
fermée, tu te fiches de moi.

723
00:49:52,072 --> 00:49:53,906
Tu veux mes talons pour aller plus vite
ou comment ça se passe ?

724
00:51:43,433 --> 00:51:45,142
Bonjour.
Parlez, uh, anglais ?

725
00:51:45,143 --> 00:51:46,686
Um, yes.

726
00:51:47,520 --> 00:51:48,562
- Sunflowers.
- Yeah.

727
00:51:48,563 --> 00:51:49,481
Excuse me.

728
00:51:50,815 --> 00:51:51,941
All of them, please.

729
00:51:52,942 --> 00:51:53,859
Tous?

730
00:51:53,860 --> 00:51:55,528
The lilies as well, please.

731
00:51:56,529 --> 00:51:57,654
I'll get all of them.

732
00:51:59,907 --> 00:52:02,577
You must have done
something really bad.

733
00:52:03,953 --> 00:52:04,954
Not yet.

734
00:52:20,387 --> 00:52:22,053
Et voici votre café, madame.

735
00:52:52,794 --> 00:52:54,712
Ça fait treize
fois que j'vous appelle.

736
00:53:07,642 --> 00:53:11,854
Mademoiselle Frank. Je vous
pris de m'excuser. Continuez l'exercise.

737
00:53:16,859 --> 00:53:17,734
Qu'est-ce qui se passe ?

738
00:53:17,735 --> 00:53:19,445
Je sais pas, Docteur,
y'a tout qui s'est éteint là...

739
00:53:19,446 --> 00:53:20,696
- Ça marche pas là-bas ?
- Non.

740
00:53:20,697 --> 00:53:22,281
Mais attends, viens,
on va aller voir.

741
00:53:22,282 --> 00:53:24,326
- J'appelle IT ?
- Oui, appelle IT.

742
00:53:32,083 --> 00:53:33,876
Excusez-moi,
le docteur Lessoir, il est où ?

743
00:53:35,712 --> 00:53:37,463
Vous faites quoi, là ? Oh !

744
00:53:37,464 --> 00:53:39,966
Ouvrez la porte !
Ouvrez la porte !

745
00:53:45,597 --> 00:53:46,888
Ouvrez cette porte !

746
00:54:01,153 --> 00:54:01,987
C'est quoi ça ?

747
00:54:01,988 --> 00:54:03,154
It's pollen.

748
00:54:03,155 --> 00:54:05,657
Mademoiselle Frank ?

749
00:54:05,658 --> 00:54:06,575
Who are you?

750
00:54:06,576 --> 00:54:08,076
Tell me where Horst Schiller is
and I'll let you out.

751
00:54:08,077 --> 00:54:09,870
Screw you.

752
00:54:11,581 --> 00:54:13,458
No.

753
00:54:13,750 --> 00:54:15,418
Ouvrez la porte !

754
00:54:16,002 --> 00:54:17,168
Mademoiselle Frank !

755
00:54:17,169 --> 00:54:18,296
No, no, no, no.

756
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:21,089
T'as appelé les flics ?
Qu'est-ce que tu fais, Miriam ?

757
00:54:24,469 --> 00:54:26,220
No, no, no.
That's not gonna work.

758
00:54:27,264 --> 00:54:28,597
Open the door.

759
00:54:28,598 --> 00:54:29,681
I'm sorry.
Not until you tell me.

760
00:54:29,682 --> 00:54:30,766
Please, just tell me
where he is.

761
00:54:30,767 --> 00:54:31,684
Ouvrez la porte !

762
00:54:32,352 --> 00:54:33,395
Why?

763
00:54:34,061 --> 00:54:35,730
Because you killed my wife.

764
00:54:36,606 --> 00:54:38,232
Her name was Sarah.

765
00:54:39,442 --> 00:54:40,692
Tell me where he is.

766
00:54:41,736 --> 00:54:44,655
Tell me!

767
00:54:44,656 --> 00:54:46,197
I don't... I don't know.

768
00:54:46,198 --> 00:54:47,909
He contacts...

769
00:54:48,701 --> 00:54:50,118
He contacts us.

770
00:54:50,119 --> 00:54:51,787
Messenger...
Messenger...

771
00:54:51,788 --> 00:54:52,913
I can't hear you.

772
00:54:54,291 --> 00:54:55,457
I can't hear you.

773
00:54:55,458 --> 00:54:56,751
Ouvrez la porte. Merde !

774
00:54:57,460 --> 00:54:58,461
Shit!

775
00:56:11,033 --> 00:56:12,702
Appelez les secours !

776
00:56:23,630 --> 00:56:24,963
Arrêtez-le ! Arrêtez-le !

777
00:56:24,964 --> 00:56:26,131
- Il lui a pris son téléphone !
- Madame ?

778
00:56:26,132 --> 00:56:27,132
Madame, vous m'entendez ?

779
00:56:56,829 --> 00:56:57,955
Shit.

780
00:57:01,834 --> 00:57:03,209
Hello. Bonjour.

781
00:57:03,210 --> 00:57:05,337
- Hello.
- Marseille, s'il vous plaît.

782
00:57:05,755 --> 00:57:07,256
37 euros, please, sir.

783
00:57:55,012 --> 00:57:56,973
What do we know
about Gretchen Frank?

784
00:57:59,391 --> 00:58:02,019
Our people say one of her
own folks ran her down.

785
00:58:03,104 --> 00:58:06,065
Most likely fallout from
when the London job went south.

786
00:58:06,941 --> 00:58:08,399
I'll let State know.

787
00:58:08,400 --> 00:58:09,735
French ambassador is asking.

788
00:58:09,736 --> 00:58:10,862
Wasn't us.

789
01:00:01,764 --> 01:00:03,724
Mais fais attention, abruti !

790
01:00:03,725 --> 01:00:04,684
Hé, t'es fou !

791
01:01:31,645 --> 01:01:32,729
You want a beer?

792
01:01:35,399 --> 01:01:36,566
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

793
01:01:36,567 --> 01:01:38,319
Deux Heineken, s'il vous plaît.

794
01:01:43,324 --> 01:01:44,991
How did you find me?

795
01:01:44,992 --> 01:01:47,661
Phone you pulled
off Gretchen Frank.

796
01:01:48,245 --> 01:01:50,039
- It's like a radar ping.
- Shit.

797
01:01:51,040 --> 01:01:52,457
Doesn't matter
how smart you are.

798
01:01:52,458 --> 01:01:55,419
If you panic, that will
always screw up a good plan.

799
01:02:04,303 --> 01:02:06,305
Then there's
the survival instinct.

800
01:02:06,763 --> 01:02:08,307
No one goes down easy.

801
01:02:09,475 --> 01:02:10,976
And, of course, the aftermath,

802
01:02:10,977 --> 01:02:14,313
when you realize you've done
something you can't undo, ever.

803
01:02:16,482 --> 01:02:17,483
I can live with that.

804
01:02:18,818 --> 01:02:19,819
You can't.

805
01:02:23,030 --> 01:02:24,114
You surprised me, Charlie.

806
01:02:24,115 --> 01:02:26,199
I can't tell you
how rare that is.

807
01:02:26,200 --> 01:02:28,410
But it ends here.

808
01:02:29,786 --> 01:02:32,498
There are no three-volley
salutes in this work.

809
01:02:33,332 --> 01:02:35,125
We're the John Does
that get found in the dumpster,

810
01:02:35,126 --> 01:02:36,792
if we get found.

811
01:02:36,793 --> 01:02:37,879
Which you won't.

812
01:02:42,633 --> 01:02:43,800
I'm sorry.

813
01:02:46,846 --> 01:02:48,472
No, those were good lessons.

814
01:02:50,807 --> 01:02:52,684
You're a good teacher, Hendo.

815
01:02:54,854 --> 01:02:56,522
I took that into account.

816
01:02:58,440 --> 01:03:00,192
Fifty-fifty odds, right?

817
01:03:01,568 --> 01:03:04,947
Did you ever account
for the things I was good at?

818
01:03:06,991 --> 01:03:08,825
Base charge on a timer.

819
01:04:15,017 --> 01:04:17,310
You have one new message.

820
01:04:18,645 --> 01:04:20,438
Meet Ottoman Cargo.

821
01:04:20,439 --> 01:04:22,941
Hangar seven.
They're expecting you.

822
01:04:22,942 --> 01:04:25,486
You'll need 500 euros in cash.

823
01:04:38,624 --> 01:04:40,583
You have one new message.

824
01:04:42,086 --> 01:04:44,505
The Fahri Cafe, Kuveloğlu Street.

825
01:04:45,256 --> 01:04:46,757
I will pass you a book.

826
01:05:42,020 --> 01:05:44,398
Wait. He is not
who you're looking for.

827
01:05:46,483 --> 01:05:47,359
Check your phone.

828
01:06:08,172 --> 01:06:09,922
It was reckless of you
to come here,

829
01:06:09,923 --> 01:06:11,425
whatever your reasons.

830
01:06:12,676 --> 01:06:13,801
Listen, I need your help.

831
01:06:13,802 --> 01:06:16,221
No. You have nowhere else to go.

832
01:06:16,222 --> 01:06:17,806
That's not the same thing.

833
01:06:19,391 --> 01:06:21,017
We're shopping, okay?

834
01:06:21,518 --> 01:06:22,644
Give me your backpack.

835
01:06:29,735 --> 01:06:30,902
And your hat.

836
01:06:32,904 --> 01:06:34,615
Now you look less American.

837
01:06:36,283 --> 01:06:37,493
What do you want?

838
01:06:39,536 --> 01:06:40,828
My wife was murdered.

839
01:06:40,829 --> 01:06:42,289
I know about your wife.

840
01:06:44,458 --> 01:06:46,793
And Paris, that was you?

841
01:06:48,754 --> 01:06:49,837
I need to find the others.

842
01:06:49,838 --> 01:06:50,922
No. Not here.

843
01:06:52,133 --> 01:06:53,549
There is a parking garage

844
01:06:53,550 --> 01:06:55,135
four blocks
from here, that way.

845
01:06:55,136 --> 01:06:56,636
First floor.

846
01:06:56,637 --> 01:06:58,929
Do some shopping, then
meet me there in half an hour.

847
01:06:58,930 --> 01:07:01,141
And if you're not followed,
we'll talk more.

848
01:07:01,142 --> 01:07:04,561
Tabii. Evet. Aynen.

849
01:07:25,123 --> 01:07:26,875
So, how long has it been you?

850
01:07:27,876 --> 01:07:28,710
Six years.

851
01:07:29,753 --> 01:07:31,879
My husband was a CIA asset.

852
01:07:31,880 --> 01:07:33,464
Former KGB.

853
01:07:33,465 --> 01:07:35,509
He was Inquiline until he died.

854
01:07:37,344 --> 01:07:38,679
He fell out of a window.

855
01:07:40,096 --> 01:07:41,181
I'm sorry.

856
01:07:41,182 --> 01:07:42,598
Accidental falls from windows

857
01:07:42,599 --> 01:07:45,185
are the number-one cause
of death of former KGB.

858
01:07:45,186 --> 01:07:46,312
You didn't know?

859
01:07:46,895 --> 01:07:48,854
He taught me
everything he was doing...

860
01:07:48,855 --> 01:07:52,776
how to mine data cache,
encrypt files.

861
01:07:54,110 --> 01:07:55,404
And after he died...

862
01:07:55,821 --> 01:07:57,363
well, I decided to keep up
my connection

863
01:07:57,364 --> 01:07:58,531
to your department...

864
01:07:58,532 --> 01:08:00,075
in case I needed help.

865
01:08:01,452 --> 01:08:03,869
Which is why I always thought
you were a middle-aged man.

866
01:08:03,870 --> 01:08:05,789
Because you were, to begin with.

867
01:08:07,333 --> 01:08:09,750
You aren't exactly
what I pictured, either.

868
01:08:09,751 --> 01:08:11,502
How did you picture me?

869
01:08:11,503 --> 01:08:12,421
I don't know.

870
01:08:13,171 --> 01:08:15,507
Mr. CIA-man-with-a-gun, I guess.

871
01:08:18,719 --> 01:08:20,011
So, you'll help me?

872
01:08:45,954 --> 01:08:47,873
It's better
than any alarm system.

873
01:08:52,794 --> 01:08:53,919
This is the first place

874
01:08:53,920 --> 01:08:56,589
I've stayed in
for more than a month...

875
01:08:56,590 --> 01:08:58,049
in the last three years.

876
01:09:00,218 --> 01:09:01,470
I don't sleep.

877
01:09:02,220 --> 01:09:04,890
But I just don't want
to run anymore.

878
01:09:07,559 --> 01:09:09,645
What makes you think
they won't find you here?

879
01:09:12,898 --> 01:09:14,232
For that night...

880
01:09:14,816 --> 01:09:15,650
when they do.

881
01:09:15,651 --> 01:09:16,776
You really think you're gonna

882
01:09:16,777 --> 01:09:18,736
fight off
the Russians with that?

883
01:09:18,737 --> 01:09:19,987
It's not for them.

884
01:09:19,988 --> 01:09:21,196
It's for me.

885
01:09:24,993 --> 01:09:26,911
Those are the three, correct?

886
01:09:26,912 --> 01:09:27,953
Yeah.

887
01:09:27,954 --> 01:09:30,122
Schiller seems
to be the coordinator.

888
01:09:30,123 --> 01:09:31,707
Ringleader.

889
01:09:31,708 --> 01:09:34,085
But he's also
the most difficult to profile.

890
01:09:34,461 --> 01:09:35,420
As far as I can tell,

891
01:09:35,421 --> 01:09:38,130
they operate as middlemen
in the proliferation chain.

892
01:09:38,131 --> 01:09:39,799
And just like the data
you showed me...

893
01:09:39,800 --> 01:09:43,218
they also source mercenaries
for Director Moore's black ops.

894
01:09:43,219 --> 01:09:46,764
Ellish sources the weapons,
but he's beyond paranoid.

895
01:09:46,765 --> 01:09:49,393
So, we have to find a way
to pull him out of the dark.

896
01:09:49,935 --> 01:09:52,603
Okay. Perhaps I can
start the conversation.

897
01:09:52,604 --> 01:09:54,606
Suggest I have
a contract for him.

898
01:09:54,981 --> 01:09:56,358
See if he will engage.

899
01:09:56,775 --> 01:09:59,110
Okay.
And this is Mishka Blazhic.

900
01:09:59,486 --> 01:10:01,070
He seems to be based in Moscow,

901
01:10:01,071 --> 01:10:02,738
but he likes
to keep on the move.

902
01:10:02,739 --> 01:10:06,327
Enjoys his luxuries.
Travels everywhere first class.

903
01:10:06,618 --> 01:10:08,035
He may be the weak link.

904
01:10:08,036 --> 01:10:09,580
Even posts online.

905
01:10:10,121 --> 01:10:11,205
This was just last week.

906
01:10:11,206 --> 01:10:14,834
No location, but
the vineyard on level ground...

907
01:10:14,835 --> 01:10:17,044
and the spacing
is wider than typical,

908
01:10:17,045 --> 01:10:19,046
so probably hotter climate.

909
01:10:19,047 --> 01:10:21,173
Chalky soil. Maybe granite.

910
01:10:21,174 --> 01:10:22,883
Low sun hitting
the wine in his glass.

911
01:10:22,884 --> 01:10:25,596
But the vineyard
would be angled north-south...

912
01:10:26,137 --> 01:10:27,389
so it's sunrise.

913
01:10:28,098 --> 01:10:31,266
And this church.
The architecture looks Spanish.

914
01:10:31,267 --> 01:10:32,477
So, hot in October.

915
01:10:32,478 --> 01:10:34,187
Maybe central Spain.

916
01:10:34,605 --> 01:10:35,981
And here, in the reflection...

917
01:10:36,523 --> 01:10:37,648
girlfriend, maybe.

918
01:10:43,154 --> 01:10:44,490
And there she is.

919
01:10:46,366 --> 01:10:47,701
Alexandra Solovoya,

920
01:10:48,452 --> 01:10:49,869
who also likes to travel.

921
01:10:49,870 --> 01:10:52,956
And she flew Moscow
to Madrid, last week.

922
01:10:53,749 --> 01:10:57,460
We need to project everything
that makes America great,

923
01:10:57,461 --> 01:10:59,336
but we need to do it openly...

924
01:10:59,337 --> 01:11:01,256
We have to assume
he's still alive.

925
01:11:01,632 --> 01:11:02,757
He has three targets.

926
01:11:02,758 --> 01:11:03,799
And so, I pledge...

927
01:11:03,800 --> 01:11:06,511
We need to locate
and get eyes on all of them.

928
01:11:06,512 --> 01:11:10,180
this agency will be
worthy of the nation's trust.

929
01:11:10,181 --> 01:11:14,019
Within our country and beyond,
we will be accountable.

930
01:11:14,561 --> 01:11:16,103
I saw your speech.

931
01:11:16,104 --> 01:11:17,188
It was excellent.

932
01:11:18,106 --> 01:11:19,649
You know,
you're the first person

933
01:11:19,650 --> 01:11:21,401
my predecessor briefed me on?

934
01:11:22,068 --> 01:11:24,695
About the stick up your ass
on ISIS, AQ,

935
01:11:24,696 --> 01:11:26,322
Iran, counterterrorism?

936
01:11:27,491 --> 01:11:30,743
Even now, three years
after mandatory retirement,

937
01:11:30,744 --> 01:11:32,245
they keep looking the other way.

938
01:11:33,079 --> 01:11:35,415
But it's housekeeping time...

939
01:11:35,999 --> 01:11:37,709
and I need to know
where you stand.

940
01:11:38,460 --> 01:11:41,754
Sounds like you're suggesting
it's time for me to go private.

941
01:11:41,755 --> 01:11:44,550
Write a neat book about my time
with the company.

942
01:11:45,676 --> 01:11:48,554
Yet here we are,
enjoying this lovely meal.

943
01:11:49,680 --> 01:11:50,763
So, why?

944
01:11:50,764 --> 01:11:51,973
Oh, please.

945
01:11:52,474 --> 01:11:54,184
I'm new, but I'm not stupid.

946
01:11:55,226 --> 01:11:57,145
I need you to be accountable.

947
01:11:57,729 --> 01:11:58,897
To me.

948
01:11:59,523 --> 01:12:02,025
Stop playing
your black ops in the sand.

949
01:12:02,358 --> 01:12:04,443
I need to be across everything.

950
01:12:04,444 --> 01:12:06,279
And I mean everything.

951
01:12:11,785 --> 01:12:12,911
Hey, Brian?

952
01:12:13,579 --> 01:12:14,829
Can you bring me
another one of these

953
01:12:14,830 --> 01:12:16,497
sourdough roll thingies?

954
01:12:16,498 --> 01:12:17,499
Sure, Mr. Moore.

955
01:12:19,334 --> 01:12:21,127
- I'll tell you a story.
- Mm.

956
01:12:21,503 --> 01:12:26,549
Your predecessor sat me down
at this very same table,

957
01:12:26,550 --> 01:12:29,093
no more than
a week into his term,

958
01:12:29,094 --> 01:12:32,764
and gave me pretty much
this exact same speech.

959
01:12:33,932 --> 01:12:34,933
Oh, wait.

960
01:12:35,726 --> 01:12:37,727
Maybe it was his predecessor.

961
01:12:37,728 --> 01:12:39,186
I can't remember.

962
01:12:39,187 --> 01:12:42,190
Anyway, I'll tell you
what I told them.

963
01:12:43,316 --> 01:12:44,776
You have my full support.

964
01:12:48,404 --> 01:12:49,531
Good.

965
01:12:50,782 --> 01:12:51,783
Good talk.

966
01:12:55,078 --> 01:12:56,329
Enjoy that pasta.

967
01:13:04,921 --> 01:13:06,130
Where?

968
01:13:06,131 --> 01:13:07,215
Madrid.

969
01:13:07,549 --> 01:13:08,633
On whose orders?

970
01:13:08,634 --> 01:13:09,843
Your lunch date.

971
01:13:14,681 --> 01:13:16,391
Let's get someone
of our own in play.

972
01:13:25,066 --> 01:13:26,400
Found him.

973
01:13:26,401 --> 01:13:28,068
At the Aguilar Hotel.

974
01:13:28,069 --> 01:13:30,614
Five stars. Nightclub.
Rooftop pool.

975
01:13:34,367 --> 01:13:35,368
What?

976
01:13:36,161 --> 01:13:37,871
Langley will be onto him, too.

977
01:13:38,872 --> 01:13:40,540
Well, then we
keep tracking him...

978
01:13:40,832 --> 01:13:42,292
until we have a clear field.

979
01:13:46,296 --> 01:13:47,755
No.

980
01:13:47,756 --> 01:13:49,215
I'm going.

981
01:13:51,426 --> 01:13:52,427
Okay.

982
01:13:54,137 --> 01:13:56,097
And keep an eye out for him.

983
01:13:56,556 --> 01:13:57,933
This is who they'll send.

984
01:14:15,742 --> 01:14:16,826
Cheers, cheers, cheers.

985
01:14:16,827 --> 01:14:18,536
Nobody walks home.
We roll home.

986
01:14:30,674 --> 01:14:31,925
He's a night swimmer.

987
01:14:32,801 --> 01:14:35,428
He pays the staff
to clear the rooftop for him.

988
01:14:45,563 --> 01:14:46,731
...the approval of the team

989
01:14:46,732 --> 01:14:49,692
and the ambitious plans
were given the green light.

990
01:14:49,693 --> 01:14:52,444
The sky pool
is suspended 16 stories

991
01:14:52,445 --> 01:14:54,239
above the ground,
which is 70 meters.

992
01:14:54,656 --> 01:14:56,073
The thickness of the clear glass

993
01:14:56,074 --> 01:14:58,951
will be 420
centimeters in total...

994
01:14:58,952 --> 01:15:00,661
made of three panels
with air gaps

995
01:15:00,662 --> 01:15:02,162
to improve the strength.

996
01:15:02,163 --> 01:15:05,499
The pool will be three
meters tall, five meters wide,

997
01:15:05,500 --> 01:15:09,755
and can hold
an impressive 150 tons of water.

998
01:15:11,131 --> 01:15:12,716
You could shoot him from there.

999
01:15:13,717 --> 01:15:15,301
You haven't seen me shoot.

1000
01:15:17,804 --> 01:15:20,347
Not for me to say here, boss,
but why bury him?

1001
01:15:20,348 --> 01:15:21,390
Why not just roll him up?

1002
01:15:21,391 --> 01:15:23,726
We're past that.
Too big of a stench.

1003
01:15:23,727 --> 01:15:26,395
Look, he practically invented
half of our surveillance tech.

1004
01:15:26,396 --> 01:15:27,981
Now, I will find him...

1005
01:15:28,648 --> 01:15:30,065
but you might have
a bigger stench on your hands

1006
01:15:30,066 --> 01:15:31,400
if he gives us the slip again.

1007
01:15:31,401 --> 01:15:33,153
You won't let that happen.

1008
01:15:37,615 --> 01:15:39,450
Charlie Heller.

1009
01:15:54,424 --> 01:15:56,467
Okay. You're going to
have to clue me in.

1010
01:15:56,802 --> 01:15:59,219
Integrity.
It's all about integrity.

1011
01:15:59,220 --> 01:16:01,305
To have morals,
something like that?

1012
01:16:01,306 --> 01:16:02,891
Yeah.
And something else as well.

1013
01:16:03,183 --> 01:16:04,935
If I have the math right.

1014
01:16:05,518 --> 01:16:06,394
I should move.

1015
01:16:30,751 --> 01:16:31,961
- Hola.
- ¿Sí?

1016
01:16:31,962 --> 01:16:33,712
Can I confirm the pool
will be ready as usual?

1017
01:16:33,713 --> 01:16:34,629
Si, Señor.

1018
01:16:34,630 --> 01:16:36,091
- Gracias.
- De nada.

1019
01:16:40,595 --> 01:16:42,638
Oh, my God.

1020
01:16:52,398 --> 01:16:53,358
Over here.

1021
01:17:02,158 --> 01:17:03,784
Second stool down at the bar.

1022
01:17:04,452 --> 01:17:05,870
Yeah. What about him?

1023
01:17:05,871 --> 01:17:06,996
He's been following me.

1024
01:17:06,997 --> 01:17:08,663
I've clocked him three times.

1025
01:17:08,664 --> 01:17:11,084
Yeah, well, where there's one,
there's always more.

1026
01:17:15,421 --> 01:17:16,255
Shit.

1027
01:17:16,256 --> 01:17:17,257
You're right.

1028
01:17:17,590 --> 01:17:18,798
Yeah, I've got your man.

1029
01:17:18,799 --> 01:17:21,761
He's in the lobby, moving
across towards the elevators.

1030
01:17:22,803 --> 01:17:25,431
And the man at the bar,
I have an ID on him.

1031
01:17:26,057 --> 01:17:28,184
Charlie, he's also CIA.

1032
01:17:28,894 --> 01:17:30,270
You have to leave now.

1033
01:17:31,229 --> 01:17:32,730
Heller, are you listening to me?

1034
01:17:34,440 --> 01:17:36,985
No. No, we go as planned.

1035
01:17:58,631 --> 01:18:00,840
I'm allowed to use the pool.

1036
01:18:00,841 --> 01:18:02,593
I paid for it.

1037
01:18:03,553 --> 01:18:05,221
Is there a problem?

1038
01:18:07,057 --> 01:18:09,600
Tell me where
to find Horst Schiller.

1039
01:18:11,311 --> 01:18:12,395
Who are you?

1040
01:18:13,438 --> 01:18:15,480
You held a gun
to my wife's head.

1041
01:18:15,481 --> 01:18:16,649
She was terrified.

1042
01:18:18,068 --> 01:18:20,069
- You have the wrong guy.
- Yeah, yeah, I know.

1043
01:18:20,070 --> 01:18:21,861
You didn't pull the trigger.

1044
01:18:21,862 --> 01:18:23,990
So, tell me where to find him.

1045
01:18:24,532 --> 01:18:26,366
If this is a joke,
I don't get it.

1046
01:18:26,367 --> 01:18:27,743
It's not a joke.

1047
01:18:28,244 --> 01:18:29,954
This is a remote
that controls a device...

1048
01:18:29,955 --> 01:18:31,205
that's been
decompressing the air

1049
01:18:31,206 --> 01:18:33,582
between the sheets
of glass beneath you.

1050
01:18:33,583 --> 01:18:36,460
If I trigger it,
the glass will shatter.

1051
01:18:36,461 --> 01:18:38,129
So, tell me where he is...

1052
01:18:38,629 --> 01:18:40,422
or swim very fast.

1053
01:18:40,423 --> 01:18:42,217
You have the wrong person.

1054
01:18:42,633 --> 01:18:43,676
No.

1055
01:18:46,012 --> 01:18:48,431
I have exactly the right person.

1056
01:19:16,126 --> 01:19:17,792
Charlie, you should
get out of there.

1057
01:19:18,711 --> 01:19:19,754
Shit.

1058
01:19:20,130 --> 01:19:21,630
Henderson's headed your way.

1059
01:19:21,631 --> 01:19:22,923
Go towards the stairwell.

1060
01:19:29,930 --> 01:19:30,847
Where is he now?

1061
01:19:30,848 --> 01:19:32,057
He's in the stairwell.

1062
01:19:32,058 --> 01:19:33,976
Three floors above.
Head towards the basement.

1063
01:19:33,977 --> 01:19:35,519
There's an exit in the back.

1064
01:19:47,032 --> 01:19:48,657
Shit! There's another one...

1065
01:19:48,658 --> 01:19:50,325
already in the basement.

1066
01:19:50,326 --> 01:19:51,618
He's coming towards you.

1067
01:19:53,829 --> 01:19:54,913
Which way? Which way?

1068
01:19:54,914 --> 01:19:56,291
Left. Go left.

1069
01:19:59,710 --> 01:20:00,878
Where is he? The other one?

1070
01:20:01,421 --> 01:20:02,797
I don't know.
I'm looking right now.

1071
01:20:03,548 --> 01:20:05,216
Heller, stop!

1072
01:20:05,758 --> 01:20:07,467
Stop! Stop.

1073
01:20:57,518 --> 01:20:58,353
Ow.

1074
01:21:28,758 --> 01:21:30,467
Charlie, you gotta
get out of there.

1075
01:21:30,468 --> 01:21:31,844
You've got--
You've got to go.

1076
01:21:32,178 --> 01:21:33,138
Right now.

1077
01:21:46,192 --> 01:21:47,359
You wanted to see me?

1078
01:21:47,360 --> 01:21:48,611
Have a seat.

1079
01:21:53,449 --> 01:21:54,784
Where's Charlie Heller?

1080
01:21:56,327 --> 01:21:58,579
As far as I know,
still on bereavement leave.

1081
01:21:59,164 --> 01:22:00,497
You talk to him at all?

1082
01:22:00,498 --> 01:22:03,000
We thought it best to give him
some space for now.

1083
01:22:03,876 --> 01:22:05,336
Makes sense.

1084
01:22:05,753 --> 01:22:07,588
I'll let you know
if we hear from him.

1085
01:22:28,609 --> 01:22:29,694
There.

1086
01:22:31,404 --> 01:22:33,280
- See that?
- Yeah. What's he doing?

1087
01:22:33,281 --> 01:22:34,282
His lips are moving.

1088
01:22:34,574 --> 01:22:35,575
Look in his ear.

1089
01:22:36,534 --> 01:22:37,784
He's talking to somebody.

1090
01:22:37,785 --> 01:22:38,869
Who?

1091
01:22:41,872 --> 01:22:43,623
Hotel security
was hacked yesterday.

1092
01:22:43,624 --> 01:22:44,916
Right. Time?

1093
01:22:44,917 --> 01:22:47,336
11:07. It was a pro job.

1094
01:22:47,337 --> 01:22:49,588
The origination
is murky at best.

1095
01:22:49,589 --> 01:22:50,715
Istanbul, perhaps.

1096
01:22:51,006 --> 01:22:51,841
Talk to me.

1097
01:22:52,342 --> 01:22:53,175
From Heller.

1098
01:22:53,801 --> 01:22:57,596
"If I had to guess, you're
a 50-year-old Russian man

1099
01:22:57,597 --> 01:22:59,932
living in Istanbul."

1100
01:23:00,975 --> 01:23:02,017
"Inquiline."

1101
01:23:02,518 --> 01:23:03,936
Code name "Inquiline."

1102
01:23:04,229 --> 01:23:05,396
Locate this person.

1103
01:23:21,161 --> 01:23:23,539
- How are you feeling?
- Eh.

1104
01:23:23,998 --> 01:23:26,208
I don't know. I-I didn't
screw up so much this time.

1105
01:23:28,210 --> 01:23:30,505
Not so sure
that's a good thing, right?

1106
01:23:32,507 --> 01:23:34,884
Actually,
I meant feeding the birds.

1107
01:23:38,012 --> 01:23:40,515
When my husband was murdered...

1108
01:23:42,099 --> 01:23:45,227
I wasn't prepared for how quiet
the world would become.

1109
01:23:46,812 --> 01:23:49,690
All the sounds that
a person makes in your life.

1110
01:23:50,275 --> 01:23:51,401
The rhythms.

1111
01:23:52,735 --> 01:23:56,322
How you expect a certain sound
at a certain time of day.

1112
01:23:57,197 --> 01:23:59,534
The door, footfall.

1113
01:24:01,327 --> 01:24:03,579
The stupid thing he used to do
that annoyed me.

1114
01:24:06,499 --> 01:24:08,042
And then suddenly there's...

1115
01:24:08,626 --> 01:24:09,752
nothing.

1116
01:24:12,963 --> 01:24:14,131
It's just great...

1117
01:24:15,007 --> 01:24:16,008
silence.

1118
01:24:18,594 --> 01:24:19,679
For me...

1119
01:24:20,680 --> 01:24:22,389
Every moment since
has been about...

1120
01:24:22,390 --> 01:24:24,475
trying to fill that silence.

1121
01:24:27,395 --> 01:24:29,104
You need to ask yourself...

1122
01:24:30,315 --> 01:24:31,566
Doing all this...

1123
01:24:33,734 --> 01:24:35,860
is it how you should fill yours?

1124
01:24:46,914 --> 01:24:48,333
Code name, Inquiline.

1125
01:24:49,208 --> 01:24:51,418
Ex-FSB by way of the KGB.

1126
01:24:51,419 --> 01:24:53,420
Flipped to us in '04.

1127
01:24:53,421 --> 01:24:55,880
- Deceased in '17.
- Deceased?

1128
01:24:55,881 --> 01:24:59,301
The Russians suspect his widow
may be operating in his place.

1129
01:25:00,720 --> 01:25:02,805
Get me the Russian station chief
in Istanbul.

1130
01:25:25,202 --> 01:25:27,663
What's wrong?

1131
01:25:29,499 --> 01:25:31,501
I want nothing from you.

1132
01:25:33,293 --> 01:25:35,336
I just want to sleep
for one night

1133
01:25:35,337 --> 01:25:37,381
with another person beside me.

1134
01:25:41,093 --> 01:25:42,177
Okay.

1135
01:26:25,971 --> 01:26:27,264
Shit.

1136
01:26:27,848 --> 01:26:29,015
- Move.
- Shit.

1137
01:26:29,016 --> 01:26:30,392
Go. Move, move.

1138
01:26:31,686 --> 01:26:33,521
This way. This way. Come on.

1139
01:26:39,318 --> 01:26:40,861
Come on. Come on.

1140
01:27:03,676 --> 01:27:05,177
Hey.

1141
01:28:10,367 --> 01:28:11,535
Have they gone?

1142
01:28:13,245 --> 01:28:14,871
It's okay. It's okay.

1143
01:28:14,872 --> 01:28:17,082
We're okay. We've lost them.

1144
01:28:18,208 --> 01:28:20,127
We're okay, we're okay,
we're okay.

1145
01:28:28,093 --> 01:28:29,468
Shit.

1146
01:28:33,683 --> 01:28:36,268
You're okay.

1147
01:28:37,853 --> 01:28:39,187
Shit.

1148
01:28:42,316 --> 01:28:43,150
Mm.

1149
01:28:49,073 --> 01:28:50,157
Shit.

1150
01:29:00,167 --> 01:29:01,001
Oh, God.

1151
01:31:51,088 --> 01:31:52,255
Heller's in Berlin.

1152
01:31:52,256 --> 01:31:53,173
What?

1153
01:31:54,508 --> 01:31:55,800
This was 40 minutes ago.

1154
01:32:23,662 --> 01:32:25,330
Yeah?

1155
01:32:26,790 --> 01:32:29,043
Put the money
on the chair. Count it.

1156
01:32:30,002 --> 01:32:32,253
Nothing until I inspect
the hardware.

1157
01:32:32,254 --> 01:32:34,298
Hardware's right there.
Go ahead.

1158
01:32:35,215 --> 01:32:36,591
Stay on the phone.

1159
01:32:38,510 --> 01:32:39,677
Shit.

1160
01:32:39,678 --> 01:32:42,096
You just armed an IED.
It's on a beam trigger.

1161
01:32:42,097 --> 01:32:46,435
You drop the lid, move away,
or cross the beam, it detonates.

1162
01:32:48,812 --> 01:32:50,104
Who the hell are you?

1163
01:32:50,105 --> 01:32:51,605
Do you honestly think
I came here alone?

1164
01:32:51,606 --> 01:32:53,316
Look at the photograph.

1165
01:32:53,317 --> 01:32:54,568
See it?

1166
01:32:55,569 --> 01:32:56,694
Do you see it?

1167
01:32:56,695 --> 01:32:58,737
Yeah, sure.
I see the photograph.

1168
01:32:58,738 --> 01:32:59,990
Do you recognize her?

1169
01:33:01,951 --> 01:33:03,577
London, maybe?

1170
01:33:04,411 --> 01:33:05,369
That's Sarah.

1171
01:33:05,370 --> 01:33:06,663
You took her life.

1172
01:33:07,414 --> 01:33:08,623
For no reason.

1173
01:33:09,208 --> 01:33:10,500
Uh...

1174
01:33:11,543 --> 01:33:13,253
Wasn't me, okay?

1175
01:33:13,545 --> 01:33:14,587
I didn't shoot her.

1176
01:33:14,588 --> 01:33:15,546
Fine.

1177
01:33:15,547 --> 01:33:16,923
Just tell me
what I need to know,

1178
01:33:16,924 --> 01:33:18,674
and I'll deactivate the device.

1179
01:33:18,675 --> 01:33:19,968
All right. Okay.
Come on, come on.

1180
01:33:19,969 --> 01:33:21,719
Where is he?
Schiller. Where is he?

1181
01:33:21,720 --> 01:33:22,761
It's impossible, man.

1182
01:33:22,762 --> 01:33:25,348
After what happened to
Gretchen and Blazhic, he's gone.

1183
01:33:25,349 --> 01:33:26,640
Horst's gone.

1184
01:33:26,641 --> 01:33:28,851
Well, then you are
of no use to me, are you?

1185
01:33:28,852 --> 01:33:30,354
No, no, no. Wait, wait, wait!

1186
01:33:33,607 --> 01:33:35,985
He'll be at sea, right?
He stays on his boat.

1187
01:33:36,360 --> 01:33:37,986
- Which sea?
- I don't know. Russian waters.

1188
01:33:37,987 --> 01:33:41,114
That's 25,000 miles
of coastline.

1189
01:33:41,115 --> 01:33:43,532
- Which sea?
- I don't know! Russian waters!

1190
01:33:43,533 --> 01:33:45,326
Not good enough. Too vague.

1191
01:33:45,327 --> 01:33:46,619
Oh, come on, man!

1192
01:33:46,620 --> 01:33:49,580
You supply him with this shit,
right? These missiles.

1193
01:33:49,581 --> 01:33:51,290
- Correct?
- Yeah.

1194
01:33:51,291 --> 01:33:53,210
Yeah? So where do you
deliver them?

1195
01:33:55,087 --> 01:33:57,964
A port on the Baltic Primorsk.

1196
01:33:57,965 --> 01:33:59,883
It's there. Okay, there's a...

1197
01:34:02,469 --> 01:34:04,679
There's a café.

1198
01:34:05,722 --> 01:34:07,681
He calls in there,
and that's it.

1199
01:34:07,682 --> 01:34:09,101
How do you contact him?

1200
01:34:10,602 --> 01:34:12,853
He uses two numbers for his men.

1201
01:34:12,854 --> 01:34:14,772
If they get the right codes,
they know it's me.

1202
01:34:14,773 --> 01:34:16,524
That's all I have.

1203
01:34:16,525 --> 01:34:17,650
We'll see.

1204
01:34:17,651 --> 01:34:18,818
Give me your phone.

1205
01:34:19,111 --> 01:34:20,320
Your phone.

1206
01:34:27,744 --> 01:34:29,245
The numbers are there.

1207
01:34:29,246 --> 01:34:30,705
The codes are by their names.

1208
01:34:37,254 --> 01:34:38,337
Their names?

1209
01:34:38,338 --> 01:34:40,506
Simon and Kristoff.

1210
01:34:40,507 --> 01:34:43,343
I'm not messing, man.
Simon and Kristoff. Come on.

1211
01:34:43,968 --> 01:34:45,886
- There. You see? See, I'm not...
- You're right.

1212
01:34:45,887 --> 01:34:48,598
I'm not lying.
Now, deactivate this thing.

1213
01:34:51,185 --> 01:34:52,561
Hey, where are you going?

1214
01:34:53,478 --> 01:34:54,353
Where you going?

1215
01:34:54,354 --> 01:34:56,730
If you jump really fast,
you might survive the blast.

1216
01:34:56,731 --> 01:34:57,816
Please!

1217
01:34:58,608 --> 01:34:59,609
Wait!

1218
01:35:00,652 --> 01:35:01,653
Wait!

1219
01:35:09,244 --> 01:35:10,703
We got a ping in Rome.

1220
01:35:10,704 --> 01:35:13,331
The little prick
is now at a museum?

1221
01:35:13,332 --> 01:35:14,666
He's not in Rome.

1222
01:35:15,375 --> 01:35:16,626
We're chasing vapors.

1223
01:35:17,169 --> 01:35:18,336
How?

1224
01:35:18,337 --> 01:35:21,214
Because they're shoveling what's
left of Mr. Lawrence Ellish

1225
01:35:21,215 --> 01:35:23,174
out of the mud in Romania.

1226
01:35:23,175 --> 01:35:24,718
He just got
on a tram in Prague.

1227
01:36:22,776 --> 01:36:24,319
You need to sleep again.

1228
01:38:28,860 --> 01:38:30,403
Are you kidding me?

1229
01:38:30,404 --> 01:38:33,155
What do you think, man?

1230
01:38:33,156 --> 01:38:34,490
Just coincidence or what?

1231
01:38:34,491 --> 01:38:36,075
Yeah, somehow, I doubt that.

1232
01:38:36,701 --> 01:38:38,035
What do you say, maybe...

1233
01:38:38,036 --> 01:38:40,871
let's go get us a cup
of shitty Russian coffee, huh?

1234
01:38:40,872 --> 01:38:42,290
Come on.

1235
01:38:42,291 --> 01:38:43,707
Look at you
in the big, bad city.

1236
01:38:43,708 --> 01:38:45,084
Come on, let's go.

1237
01:38:46,085 --> 01:38:47,796
So, a rabbit on the run, huh?

1238
01:38:55,053 --> 01:38:55,929
Sit down, man.

1239
01:39:04,020 --> 01:39:05,771
So, you're here to kill me?

1240
01:39:05,772 --> 01:39:07,981
Nah, that's not really
what I do.

1241
01:39:07,982 --> 01:39:09,483
I mean, I might set you up
to get killed.

1242
01:39:09,484 --> 01:39:10,984
You know, facilitate it.

1243
01:39:10,985 --> 01:39:12,487
What are you looking for?

1244
01:39:14,823 --> 01:39:15,948
I don't know, my assassin?

1245
01:39:15,949 --> 01:39:18,826
Your assassin?
Yeah, and what do you think?

1246
01:39:18,827 --> 01:39:20,077
What does an assassin look like?

1247
01:39:20,078 --> 01:39:22,538
I mean,
it can kinda be anyone, huh?

1248
01:39:22,539 --> 01:39:24,582
I mean,
even a slight little nerdy fella

1249
01:39:24,583 --> 01:39:26,542
- likes to work on computers.
- Mm.

1250
01:39:26,543 --> 01:39:27,960
Only thing dangerous
about him is

1251
01:39:27,961 --> 01:39:30,671
he's got this dream
about rehabbing a Cessna,

1252
01:39:30,672 --> 01:39:34,091
just to fly it around to prove
to himself that he's not afraid.

1253
01:39:39,889 --> 01:39:41,224
These are killer, by the way.

1254
01:39:42,559 --> 01:39:44,436
Mm.
I'm gonna show you something.

1255
01:39:46,813 --> 01:39:47,855
Uh-oh.

1256
01:39:47,856 --> 01:39:50,359
I gotta hand it to you.
I almost didn't recognize you.

1257
01:39:50,984 --> 01:39:53,527
I said to the team, "Nah,
there's no way. That ain't him."

1258
01:39:53,528 --> 01:39:54,570
What do you want?

1259
01:39:54,571 --> 01:39:56,072
Honestly...

1260
01:39:57,115 --> 01:39:58,574
just here to save your life.

1261
01:39:58,575 --> 01:39:59,659
Oh.

1262
01:40:00,744 --> 01:40:02,244
How are you gonna do that?

1263
01:40:02,245 --> 01:40:03,705
Chuck, you killed three people.

1264
01:40:04,205 --> 01:40:06,624
Are you done?
Have you had enough?

1265
01:40:06,625 --> 01:40:08,501
No. I want the guy who pulled
the trigger. I want 'em all.

1266
01:40:08,502 --> 01:40:09,877
Damn, dude.

1267
01:40:09,878 --> 01:40:11,879
Well, that's
pretty cold-blooded.

1268
01:40:11,880 --> 01:40:14,382
You think they're gonna
let you leave Russia?

1269
01:40:14,383 --> 01:40:16,299
I mean, how does that even work?
How do you leave here?

1270
01:40:16,300 --> 01:40:17,801
The only way you leave here
is in a box.

1271
01:40:17,802 --> 01:40:20,262
But if you walk out of here
right now with me,

1272
01:40:20,263 --> 01:40:21,889
I can help you.

1273
01:40:21,890 --> 01:40:23,850
Nobody sent me.
I'm here on my own.

1274
01:40:24,976 --> 01:40:26,560
Shit, maybe you got a future
in this field.

1275
01:40:26,561 --> 01:40:28,395
Maybe we can figure
something out like that, huh?

1276
01:40:28,396 --> 01:40:29,605
Just come home with me.

1277
01:40:29,606 --> 01:40:31,065
I have a future in the field?

1278
01:40:32,567 --> 01:40:35,319
Well, I could have sworn
you just said I have no future.

1279
01:40:36,320 --> 01:40:37,696
Look, I'm not gonna sit here
and pretend like

1280
01:40:37,697 --> 01:40:38,989
I understand
what's goin' on with you.

1281
01:40:38,990 --> 01:40:40,658
I don't, okay?
I've never felt that.

1282
01:40:40,659 --> 01:40:42,201
Your loss, I get it.

1283
01:40:43,202 --> 01:40:44,745
But you honored her.

1284
01:40:44,746 --> 01:40:45,829
What do you think she wants?

1285
01:40:45,830 --> 01:40:47,164
You think she wants you
to die here

1286
01:40:47,165 --> 01:40:49,000
in this country
with these people?

1287
01:40:49,876 --> 01:40:51,210
She would want you home, man.

1288
01:40:52,712 --> 01:40:53,713
No. I--

1289
01:40:54,422 --> 01:40:55,549
I can't go home.

1290
01:40:56,966 --> 01:40:57,967
Why?

1291
01:40:59,886 --> 01:41:01,763
She's not-- She's not there.

1292
01:41:09,103 --> 01:41:10,188
Okay.

1293
01:41:10,814 --> 01:41:12,940
You keep your head
on a swivel now, okay, Chuck?

1294
01:41:12,941 --> 01:41:13,942
Mm.

1295
01:42:21,384 --> 01:42:22,676
Sir, I'm sor-- sorry.

1296
01:42:22,677 --> 01:42:24,095
Do you speak English?

1297
01:42:25,722 --> 01:42:27,681
Sorry, sir. I'm sorry.

1298
01:42:27,682 --> 01:42:29,267
There were two men.

1299
01:42:30,184 --> 01:42:32,353
With you on a truck.

1300
01:44:38,021 --> 01:44:40,313
It's not very impressive, is it?

1301
01:44:40,314 --> 01:44:43,234
Placed near the cargo
you have below those hatches?

1302
01:44:43,985 --> 01:44:47,113
I think I might even feel
a little insulted.

1303
01:44:49,240 --> 01:44:51,159
- Who's coming after me?
- Me.

1304
01:44:51,826 --> 01:44:54,245
- Me. I'm coming after you.
- Mm.

1305
01:44:54,871 --> 01:44:56,289
And who is running you?

1306
01:44:56,748 --> 01:44:58,540
What, are you afraid
Director Moore

1307
01:44:58,541 --> 01:45:00,709
has finally decided
to call it quits?

1308
01:45:00,710 --> 01:45:02,503
- Have you shut down?
- Mm.

1309
01:45:02,921 --> 01:45:04,629
Whatever you think you know...

1310
01:45:04,630 --> 01:45:07,299
I know Moore and Caleb
hire you and your outfit

1311
01:45:07,300 --> 01:45:08,801
to carry out black ops for them.

1312
01:45:08,802 --> 01:45:09,969
I have proof.

1313
01:45:10,469 --> 01:45:15,599
But, uh, that's not
what this is about, is it?

1314
01:45:16,976 --> 01:45:17,811
No.

1315
01:45:21,064 --> 01:45:23,316
I came here
to face my wife's killer.

1316
01:45:25,568 --> 01:45:27,195
To look him in the eyes.

1317
01:45:28,362 --> 01:45:30,656
And tell him she mattered.

1318
01:45:32,867 --> 01:45:34,493
Sarah mattered.

1319
01:45:36,287 --> 01:45:39,123
So, it is just you. Hmm?

1320
01:45:40,959 --> 01:45:44,002
Gretchen, Blazhic, Ellish...

1321
01:45:44,003 --> 01:45:46,588
the men that, uh,
they sent after you.

1322
01:45:46,589 --> 01:45:49,925
This whole thing
is all your revenge?

1323
01:45:49,926 --> 01:45:51,886
Charlie's revenge?

1324
01:45:56,808 --> 01:45:57,892
Please.

1325
01:46:08,862 --> 01:46:11,530
I, uh-- I remember your wife.

1326
01:46:13,616 --> 01:46:15,701
She took the place
of someone else.

1327
01:46:15,994 --> 01:46:17,745
It's very, very brave.

1328
01:46:18,872 --> 01:46:21,415
I am sorry she died.

1329
01:46:21,707 --> 01:46:23,458
But it was...

1330
01:46:23,459 --> 01:46:24,543
necessary.

1331
01:46:25,044 --> 01:46:27,130
The police had blocked our exit.

1332
01:46:27,964 --> 01:46:31,466
I had to demonstrate
what would happen

1333
01:46:31,467 --> 01:46:33,887
if they did not allow us
to leave.

1334
01:46:34,387 --> 01:46:35,763
That-- That's it?

1335
01:46:38,641 --> 01:46:39,767
"Necessary"?

1336
01:46:40,518 --> 01:46:43,270
You are not
so different to me...

1337
01:46:43,271 --> 01:46:47,400
killing these people
to find your way here to me.

1338
01:46:48,651 --> 01:46:50,403
Has it made you feel better?

1339
01:46:51,737 --> 01:46:53,406
I won't know
till I've killed you.

1340
01:46:56,993 --> 01:46:58,286
It was...

1341
01:46:59,370 --> 01:47:01,829
- an instant. Your wife.
- No, it wasn't.

1342
01:47:01,830 --> 01:47:03,706
Yet you tortured
my colleagues...

1343
01:47:03,707 --> 01:47:06,209
dropped a man 16 stories...

1344
01:47:06,210 --> 01:47:09,754
suffocated a woman
in a-- a locked chamber.

1345
01:47:09,755 --> 01:47:12,299
You had them all unarmed, defenseless.

1346
01:47:12,300 --> 01:47:16,803
Staged your elaborate murders
from a distance.

1347
01:47:16,804 --> 01:47:18,556
And you know why?

1348
01:47:21,475 --> 01:47:22,643
I do.

1349
01:47:24,020 --> 01:47:28,066
Because it's hard
to take a life up close.

1350
01:47:28,816 --> 01:47:33,196
You lose something each time.

1351
01:47:33,571 --> 01:47:36,740
A piece of yourself
you cannot get back ever.

1352
01:47:38,659 --> 01:47:41,995
And you've lost so much already.

1353
01:47:41,996 --> 01:47:44,456
So, you had to
give them a chance

1354
01:47:44,457 --> 01:47:45,832
to escape the mouse trap...

1355
01:47:45,833 --> 01:47:48,877
to run just fast enough.

1356
01:47:50,713 --> 01:47:52,714
Because then
you can tell yourself

1357
01:47:52,715 --> 01:47:55,133
there's no blood on your hands.

1358
01:47:55,134 --> 01:47:58,511
But doesn't mean you're weak.

1359
01:47:58,512 --> 01:48:02,766
Just means
you are not truly a killer.

1360
01:48:05,894 --> 01:48:07,313
Don't believe me?

1361
01:48:21,577 --> 01:48:22,578
Go ahead.

1362
01:48:23,579 --> 01:48:26,415
You're here to kill me.
Take it. You'll see.

1363
01:48:28,292 --> 01:48:30,253
It's not a trick. Here.

1364
01:48:34,340 --> 01:48:36,384
All right, then. Huh?

1365
01:48:37,301 --> 01:48:39,178
End it face-to-face.

1366
01:48:43,099 --> 01:48:44,599
A friend of mine once told me

1367
01:48:44,600 --> 01:48:46,519
I'd never be able
to pull the trigger.

1368
01:48:48,604 --> 01:48:52,525
But he also said
I'd never be able to kill.

1369
01:49:33,316 --> 01:49:34,775
There it is.

1370
01:49:37,945 --> 01:49:39,655
That's what I came here for.

1371
01:49:41,365 --> 01:49:43,451
To balance the scales.

1372
01:49:46,620 --> 01:49:50,333
To make you feel what she felt
in that moment.

1373
01:49:51,709 --> 01:49:53,419
Before you killed her.

1374
01:50:20,529 --> 01:50:21,530
Was ist das?

1375
01:50:29,788 --> 01:50:31,124
Was ist das?

1376
01:50:32,040 --> 01:50:33,291
I've taken us on a detour.

1377
01:50:33,292 --> 01:50:35,001
Huh? Bullshit.

1378
01:50:35,002 --> 01:50:37,338
I've taken control of your boat.

1379
01:50:38,005 --> 01:50:39,757
We've just reached
Finnish waters.

1380
01:50:43,427 --> 01:50:45,179
That is not possible.

1381
01:50:45,763 --> 01:50:47,889
This ship is a vault.

1382
01:50:47,890 --> 01:50:50,142
Your own CIA insisted upon it.

1383
01:50:50,143 --> 01:50:52,060
Using encryption I wrote.

1384
01:50:52,770 --> 01:50:54,687
Look, it's all running
from my hotel room.

1385
01:50:54,688 --> 01:50:56,856
These two may have
smashed my phone,

1386
01:50:56,857 --> 01:50:58,401
but they held on to theirs...

1387
01:50:58,776 --> 01:51:00,067
and my watch.

1388
01:51:00,068 --> 01:51:02,821
So, I'm the transmitter
and you...

1389
01:51:03,531 --> 01:51:04,948
you invited me in.

1390
01:51:05,699 --> 01:51:08,827
I just needed you to talk as
long as it took to get us here.

1391
01:51:12,165 --> 01:51:15,501
That would be
the Finnish Navy and Interpol.

1392
01:51:15,793 --> 01:51:17,378
I gave them this location.

1393
01:51:20,673 --> 01:51:22,965
We are boarding your boat.

1394
01:51:22,966 --> 01:51:26,762
We are acting in accordance
with international law.

1395
01:51:27,471 --> 01:51:30,140
You are being placed
under arrest.

1396
01:51:34,812 --> 01:51:36,605
Stand down, stand down!

1397
01:51:38,106 --> 01:51:39,232
Down.

1398
01:51:41,527 --> 01:51:42,527
Heller.

1399
01:51:42,528 --> 01:51:43,820
Charlie Heller.

1400
01:51:46,199 --> 01:51:48,325
All right.

1401
01:52:54,308 --> 01:52:56,018
When I took up this role...

1402
01:52:56,852 --> 01:52:59,979
I made it clear to everyone
who works in this building,

1403
01:52:59,980 --> 01:53:01,981
that even though our work

1404
01:53:01,982 --> 01:53:04,817
sometimes goes on
in dark corners,

1405
01:53:04,818 --> 01:53:07,404
that is no excuse
to allow darkness

1406
01:53:07,405 --> 01:53:10,741
to obscure our objectives
or our methods.

1407
01:53:12,285 --> 01:53:14,536
So, I'm deeply saddened
to have to tell you

1408
01:53:14,537 --> 01:53:16,996
that information has surfaced

1409
01:53:16,997 --> 01:53:19,541
that implicates senior members
of this agency

1410
01:53:19,542 --> 01:53:21,919
in carrying out
rogue missions,

1411
01:53:22,295 --> 01:53:24,629
which put the safety
of our own operators

1412
01:53:24,630 --> 01:53:27,382
and agents we work with
at great risk.

1413
01:53:27,383 --> 01:53:28,551
Gentlemen.

1414
01:53:28,967 --> 01:53:32,095
The cost of winning
the war cannot be our honor.

1415
01:53:32,763 --> 01:53:34,848
Those operations
were not sanctioned.

1416
01:53:35,599 --> 01:53:37,435
They were illegal.

1417
01:53:37,768 --> 01:53:40,521
And those individuals will face
the full force of the law.

1418
01:53:41,730 --> 01:53:43,231
I will now take questions.

1419
01:53:43,649 --> 01:53:44,567
Washington Post.

1420
01:53:45,067 --> 01:53:46,568
I understand these arrests
are linked to...

1421
01:53:46,569 --> 01:53:49,571
a series of killings
in European cities last year.

1422
01:53:49,572 --> 01:53:52,114
Was the CIA involved
in those operations?

1423
01:53:52,115 --> 01:53:54,701
You would not expect me
to answer that.

1424
01:53:54,702 --> 01:53:56,578
NBC. Is the whistleblower

1425
01:53:56,579 --> 01:53:58,413
still employed by the agency?

1426
01:53:58,414 --> 01:54:00,999
I can confirm
that the officer is safe.

1427
01:54:01,417 --> 01:54:03,836
And that they will continue
to serve with the agency.

1428
01:54:47,755 --> 01:54:49,339
Who's the Uber driver now?

1429
01:54:51,216 --> 01:54:52,675
You must be
running out of lives.

1430
01:54:54,803 --> 01:54:56,639
And you keep on
surprising me, Charlie.

1431
01:54:57,598 --> 01:54:58,765
Everything you taught me.

1432
01:54:58,766 --> 01:55:02,184
No, no. What you've done,
what you've become...

1433
01:55:02,185 --> 01:55:03,646
can't teach that.

1434
01:55:05,313 --> 01:55:07,815
I guess I just suddenly saw
what needed doing.

1435
01:55:07,816 --> 01:55:08,901
Yeah.

1436
01:55:09,652 --> 01:55:11,319
When no one else did.

1437
01:55:12,571 --> 01:55:13,572
Thank you.

1438
01:55:19,912 --> 01:55:21,622
See you around, Charlie.

